Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.78,0:00:30.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,MOSFILM
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.37,0:00:38.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Second Artists' Association
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.14,0:00:56.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Alisa Freindlikh
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.19,0:01:03.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Aleksandr Kaidanovsky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.86,0:01:10.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Anatoly Solonitsyn
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.16,0:01:16.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nikolai Grinko
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.37,0:01:21.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,in the film
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.33,0:01:28.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,STALKER
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.51,0:01:37.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Scenario:\NArkady Strugatsky, Boris Strugatsky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.18,0:01:42.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Adapted from the novel\NRoadside Picnic
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.52,0:01:49.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Director: Andrei Tarkovsky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.74,0:01:56.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Photography: Alexander Knyazhinsky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.04,0:02:03.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Art Direction: Andrei Tarkovsky
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:10.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Music: Eduard Artemyev
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.55,0:02:15.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Assistant Director: L. Tarkovskaya
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.80,0:02:22.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Poems by F.I. Tiutchev\Nand Arseny Tarkovsky
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.77,0:02:26.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sound: V. Sharun
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.73,0:02:29.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Conductor: E. Khachturyan
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.74,0:02:35.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Makeup: V. Lvov\NFilm Editing: L. Feyginova
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.41,0:02:38.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Costume Design: N. Fomina
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.30,0:03:45.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,STALKER
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.68,0:03:48.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Was it a meteorite\Nor a visitation from outer space?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.19,0:03:52.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Whatever it was, in our small country,\Nthere appeared a miracle — the Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.98,0:03:57.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,We sent in troops. Not one returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.36,0:04:03.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then we surrounded the Zone\Nwith a security cordon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.29,0:04:05.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,We did right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.33,0:04:09.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Although I'm not sure. I'm not sure."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.88,0:04:14.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,From an interview with Nobel Prize winner\NProfessor Wallace to an RAI correspondent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.79,0:10:21.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why did you take my watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.04,0:10:27.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:35.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,You gave me your word. | believed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.89,0:10:42.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,You won't think of yourself.\NBut what about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.27,0:10:46.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Think about your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.52,0:10:52.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,She's not even used to you yet,\Nand you're going back to your old ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.82,0:11:00.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've turned me into an old hag,\Nruined my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.12,0:11:03.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Quiet. You'll wake up Monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:08.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,| can't spend my life waiting for you.\NIl die.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.23,0:11:25.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,You were going to get proper work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.85,0:11:29.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,They promised you a decent, normal job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.94,0:11:35.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll be back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.32,0:11:39.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll be back in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.58,0:11:42.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Next time, they'll give you ten years\Ninstead of five.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.45,0:11:44.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,And you'll have nothing to show\Nfor those ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.91,0:11:46.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not the Zone, not anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.75,0:11:51.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,And in ten years, I'll be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.63,0:11:57.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Prison"? I'm imprisoned everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.14,0:12:03.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let me go.\N- | won't let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.02,0:12:05.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Let me go.\N- | won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.49,0:12:16.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go on, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.16,0:12:20.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,And may you rot there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.33,0:12:25.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,| curse the day | met you, you scum!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.20,0:12:29.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,God cursed you by sending you that child.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:34.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,And he cursed me because of you.\NYou bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.59,0:13:24.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,My dear, the world\Nis so unutterably boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.55,0:13:29.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's no telepathy, no ghosts,\Nno flying saucers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.14,0:13:31.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,They can't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.90,0:13:34.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,The world is ruled by cast-iron laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.61,0:13:39.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,These laws are not broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.24,0:13:41.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,They just can't be broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.49,0:13:47.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't hope for flying saucers.\NThat would be too interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.25,0:13:50.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,But what about the Bermuda Triangle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.37,0:13:53.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're not going to contradict...\N- Yes, | am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.92,0:13:56.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,There is no Bermuda Triangle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.34,0:13:57.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's Triangle ABC,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.88,0:14:01.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,which equals\NTriangle A prime, B prime, C prime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.80,0:14:05.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's all so tedious, so very tedious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.56,0:14:09.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,In the Middle Ages, life was interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.60,0:14:14.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Every house had its goblin,\Neach church had God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.23,0:14:18.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,People were young.\NNow every fourth person is old.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.48,0:14:21.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's boring, my angel. It's so boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.61,0:14:26.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,But you said that the Zone is the product\Nof a super civilization —
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.91,0:14:32.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which is probably also boring,\Nalso with laws and triangles,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.25,0:14:35.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,but without goblins\Nand, of course, without any God.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.25,0:14:41.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because if there is a God,\Nhe'll be that very triangle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.72,0:14:45.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then | simply don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.68,0:14:52.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's for me. Good-bye, dear friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.27,0:14:58.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,This fine lady agreed\Nto go with us into the Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.48,0:15:01.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,She's so brave. Her name is —
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.49,0:15:04.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, what is your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.86,0:15:07.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you really a stalker?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.16,0:15:16.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll explain everything later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.97,0:15:26.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.77,0:15:36.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,An idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.69,0:15:43.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you've been drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.11,0:15:49.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,| simply had a drink,\Nas does half of all humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.20,0:15:53.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the other half also gets drunk,\Nincluding women and children.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.16,0:15:55.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,| simply had a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.77,0:16:19.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Someone spilled something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.24,0:16:36.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Drink. It's still early.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.08,0:16:42.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,How about one for the road?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.42,0:16:45.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.48,0:17:05.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Take it away.\N- Of course, the prohibition law.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.28,0:17:07.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Alcohol is the scourge of mankind."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.78,0:17:09.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's drink beer then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.32,0:17:13.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is he coming with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.91,0:17:18.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. He'll sober up.\NHe needs to go there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.50,0:17:30.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Are you really a professor?\N- If you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.34,0:17:35.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,In that case, let me introduce myself.\NMy name is —
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.81,0:17:38.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,They call him the Writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.48,0:17:40.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,And what's my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.94,0:17:43.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're the professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.61,0:17:46.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:50.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm a writer, so naturally\Neveryone calls me the Writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.24,0:17:55.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What do you write about?\N- About my readers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.12,0:17:57.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,No sense in writing about anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.58,0:18:00.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's no sense\Nin writing about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.87,0:18:05.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you? A chemist?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:08.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'd say a physicist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.92,0:18:12.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's probably tedious, too.\NSearching for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.55,0:18:18.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,You dig here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.35,0:18:22.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Right. The nucleus consists of protons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.52,0:18:24.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's a good dig.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.69,0:18:28.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Triangle ABC\Nequals Triangle A prime, B prime, C prime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.53,0:18:31.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,But with me, it's a different matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.65,0:18:38.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,| dig for the truth, but, while | do,\Nsomething happens to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.54,0:18:42.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,The truth changes into a pile of —
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.67,0:18:45.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,| won't say what.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.13,0:18:53.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's just fine for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.34,0:18:56.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Say there's some antique pot in a museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.89,0:18:59.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,In its own time, it was a trash bin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.68,0:19:06.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,But now it draws admiration for\Nits simplicity of line and unique form.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.40,0:19:10.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,And everyone oohs and aahs over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.69,0:19:14.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, it turns out\Nnot to be an antique at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.07,0:19:19.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,It was planted by some joker for a laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.08,0:19:25.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,The sounds of admiration die away.\NSome connoisseurs!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.25,0:19:28.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is what you think about all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.00,0:19:33.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,God forbid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.21,0:19:36.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,| seldom think. It's bad for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.18,0:19:41.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to write and keep\Nthinking about success or failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.10,0:19:42.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Naturlich.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.56,0:19:46.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,But on the other hand, if my books\Naren't being read in 100 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.73,0:19:48.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,why bother to write?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.52,0:19:56.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Professor, why did you\Nget involved in this business?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.11,0:19:59.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's the Zone to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.45,0:20:02.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, in a sense, I'm a scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.33,0:20:07.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's in it for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.71,0:20:10.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,A fashionable author...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.46,0:20:14.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,...women draped all over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.34,0:20:17.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've lost my inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.63,0:20:19.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm going to beg for some.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.89,0:20:23.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you've exhausted your talent?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.31,0:20:27.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,What? Yes, in a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.35,0:20:32.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you hear that? That's our train.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.12,0:20:42.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did you take the top off the car?\N- It's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.05,0:20:57.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Rueger.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.59,0:21:03.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,If | don't come back, tell my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.53,0:21:21.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Damn! | forgot to buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.99,0:21:24.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:28.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What is it?\N- Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.87,0:21:32.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You're all like that.\N- Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.33,0:21:34.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,You believe any superstitious rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.71,0:21:38.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,l'll have to save these for a rainy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.68,0:21:43.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you really a scientist?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.03,0:23:22.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.16,0:23:27.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Keep still!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.27,0:23:59.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,See if anyone's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.86,0:24:07.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hurry, for God's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.79,0:24:15.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's nobody here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.71,0:24:17.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go to the other door.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.65,0:24:46.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get going, Writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.45,0:27:00.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Keep your eyes open.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.09,0:27:58.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did you bring the gasoline can?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.59,0:28:00.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes. A full one.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.19,0:28:16.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,What | said about going there...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.86,0:28:22.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's all a lie.\N| don't give a damn about inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.49,0:28:27.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,But how can | put a name to...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.62,0:28:30.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,...what it is that | want?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.59,0:28:34.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,How am | to Know | don't want what | want
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.05,0:28:39.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,or that | really don't want\Nwhat | don't want?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.60,0:28:43.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,These are intangibles where\Nthe moment you name them,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.60,0:28:48.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,their meaning evaporates\Nlike jellyfish in the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.44,0:28:49.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've seen them around.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.19,0:28:54.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,My consciousness\Nwants the triumph of vegetarianism.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.90,0:28:58.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,My subconscious longs for a juicy steak.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.32,0:29:00.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,So what do | want?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.37,0:29:06.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,| want world supremacy, at the very least.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.37,0:29:12.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why do they need a train in the Zone?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.92,0:29:18.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,It won't go beyond the military post.\NThe guards won't venture in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.18,0:29:28.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Everyone in their places?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.43,0:30:43.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.77,0:31:45.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen. Go and see\Nif there's a railcar there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.32,0:31:47.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What railcar?\N- Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.55,0:32:12.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get back. I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.13,0:34:10.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,The gasoline can.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.03,0:34:37.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.62,0:34:42.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Leave your rucksack. It's in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.41,0:34:44.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,| see you're traveling light.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.96,0:34:52.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,If anyone's hit, don't cry out.\NIf they spot you, they'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.38,0:34:57.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then when everything's quiet,\Ncrawl back to the post.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.47,0:34:58.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll be picked up later.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.16,0:35:16.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Won't they come after us?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.95,0:35:20.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, they're scared to death of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.58,0:35:22.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.05,0:39:46.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here we are, home at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.81,0:39:52.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's so still.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.98,0:39:57.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's the quietest place on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.31,0:40:01.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll see for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.15,0:40:07.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's so beautiful. There's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.20,0:40:08.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.78,0:40:12.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Three men can't foul it up in one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.20,0:40:14.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why can't we? Sure we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.13,0:40:21.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Strange, the flowers have no scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.00,0:40:25.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't you feel it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.51,0:40:28.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,It stinks like a swamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.34,0:40:30.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, that's the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.18,0:40:38.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,There used to be flower beds here,\Nbut Porcupine trampled on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.90,0:40:43.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,But their scent lingered on\Nfor many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.11,0:40:48.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why did he wipe them out?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.70,0:40:50.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,| don't Know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.99,0:40:53.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,| asked him why.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.08,0:40:57.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,He said, "One day, you'll understand."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.17,0:41:03.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,| think he simply began to hate the Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.38,0:41:11.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is Porcupine his real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.47,0:41:14.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, a nickname. Like yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.89,0:41:19.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,For years he brought people into the Zone,\Nand nobody could stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.40,0:41:21.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.23,0:41:25.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,He opened my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.65,0:41:32.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,They didn't call him Porcupine then,\Nbut Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.45,0:41:39.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then something happened to him.\NSomething broke inside him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.38,0:41:43.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,| think he was being punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.92,0:41:48.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Help me. Tie the bandage strips\Nto these metal nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.09,0:41:53.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,ll just take a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.81,0:41:56.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,| need...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.78,0:42:12.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Be careful when you walk here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.79,0:42:20.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.71,0:42:23.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he just wants to be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.00,0:42:28.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why? Even with three of us here,\N| feel uneasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.13,0:42:33.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's back in the Zone.\NRemember, he's a stalker.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.64,0:42:37.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,What of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.56,0:42:42.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,You see, stalking is a kind of vocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.48,0:42:47.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,- | imagined stalkers to be different.\N- How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.23,0:42:52.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Like Leatherstocking\Nor Chingachgook or Big Snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.11,0:42:55.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Our stalker's biography\Nis more terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.66,0:42:59.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was in prison several times,\Nand he was crippled here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.33,0:43:02.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,His daughter is a mutant,\Na so-called Zone victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.83,0:43:04.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,They say she has no legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.88,0:43:11.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,What did he mean about the Porcupine?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.47,0:43:15.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,What did he mean he was punished?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.01,0:43:17.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,What is that, a figure of speech?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.77,0:43:23.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,One fine day,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.56,0:43:26.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Porcupine returned from this place
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.90,0:43:28.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,and suddenly became rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.03,0:43:32.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Incredibly rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.69,0:43:34.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,You call that a punishment?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.36,0:43:39.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Within a week, he had hanged himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.58,0:43:41.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Why?\N- Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.54,0:43:47.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.33,0:45:48.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,About 20 years ago,\Nthey say a meteorite fell here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.46,0:45:51.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,It razed the settlement.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.04,0:45:57.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,They searched for it,\Nbut they found nothing, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.34,0:46:01.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why "of course"?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.76,0:46:03.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then people began to vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.39,0:46:10.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Finally, it was decided —\N- Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.19,0:46:13.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Finally, it was decided
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.23,0:46:18.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,that this meteorite\Nwas not quite a meteorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.86,0:46:20.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, for a start...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.11,0:46:28.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,...they put up barbed wire to stop\Nthe inquisitive taking risks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.46,0:46:36.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then rumors began that somewhere\Nin the Zone there's a place...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.51,0:46:41.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,...where desires come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.34,0:46:48.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, naturally, they started\Nto guard the Zone like a treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.73,0:46:54.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,For who knows what desires\Na person might have?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.40,0:46:58.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,What was it if it wasn't a meteorite?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.86,0:47:03.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.24,0:47:07.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,But what do you think it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.37,0:47:13.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,| don't have any idea.\NIt could have been anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.46,0:47:19.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,A message to mankind,\Nas a colleague of mine says.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.67,0:47:21.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Or a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.26,0:47:28.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Some gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.43,0:47:31.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why would they want to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.68,0:47:33.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,To make us happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.11,0:47:42.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,The flowers are blooming again,\Nbut they've no scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.32,0:47:48.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Forgive me for leaving you here,\Nbut it was too early to go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.08,0:47:54.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.42,0:47:59.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Maybe there are people living here.\N- Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.46,0:48:04.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,You told me the story yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.97,0:48:10.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Those travelers who were here\Nwhen the Zone appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.56,0:48:13.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's no one in the Zone.\NThere can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.02,0:48:19.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are we ready to start?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.90,0:49:08.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,How do we get back?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.41,0:49:12.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Nobody finds their way back from here.\N- What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.16,0:49:16.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll proceed as agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.25,0:49:25.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Each time, I'll point out the path.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.21,0:49:27.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous to veer from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.76,0:49:32.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Keep the last pole in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.39,0:49:36.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,You go first, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.07,0:49:50.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.79,0:50:01.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Try to follow in his tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.12,0:51:22.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Lord! Where's —
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.58,0:51:27.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did they remain here, the people?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.29,0:51:31.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.09,0:51:36.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,| only recall them leaving\Nfrom our station to come here to the Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.14,0:51:39.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,| was still a kid then.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.60,0:51:43.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Everyone thought\Nsomeone wanted to conquer us.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.69,0:51:52.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go on, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.04,0:52:02.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now you, Writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.77,0:54:34.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Room is over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.82,0:54:38.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,We go this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.86,0:54:43.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to make it seem hard?\NYou can almost wrap your arms around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.03,0:54:48.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, but you need very long arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.91,0:54:51.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,We don't have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.11,0:56:00.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Leave it!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.44,0:56:04.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't — Don't touch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.78,0:56:09.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,| said don't touch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.03,0:56:14.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,What, are you crazy?\NWhat was that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.75,0:56:19.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,| said this wasn't the place for a stroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.67,0:56:23.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Zone demands respect,\Notherwise it'll punish you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.59,0:56:27.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't try anything like that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.34,0:56:29.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Has the cat got your tongue?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.97,0:56:33.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,- | asked you not to.\N- Do we go this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.48,0:56:40.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes. To the left.\NBut we don't go in a direct line.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.44,0:56:44.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll go roundabout.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.90,0:56:47.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.82,0:56:52.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here, the straight path isn't shortest.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.99,0:56:55.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,The more indirect, the less risk there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.54,0:56:57.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is it fatal to go straight anead?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.54,0:57:00.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,- | told you. It's dangerous.\N- Is the detour less dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.00,0:57:03.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's not, but nobody goes straight...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.21,0:57:04.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,You and your detours!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.55,0:57:08.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,How about if | just go straight?\N- Listen. You —
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.34,0:57:12.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why can't we go straight ahead?\NIt's right under our noses.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.43,0:57:15.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's risky here, risky there.\NWhat the hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.93,0:57:19.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know your attitude about this\Nis very irresponsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.27,0:57:24.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm fed up with your nuts and bandages.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.53,0:57:28.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Forget it. I'm going this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.45,0:57:31.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,- The man's crazy.\N- And | return the compliment.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.12,0:57:33.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,May |?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.80,0:57:47.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,The wind is rising.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.26,0:57:51.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you feel it? The grass...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.73,0:58:04.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, all the more reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.86,0:58:06.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.08,0:58:25.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hold it.\N- Take your hands off me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.80,0:58:27.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.09,0:58:32.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then let the professor be my witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.34,0:58:35.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm didn't send you in there.\NYou're going of your own free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.01,0:58:38.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of my own free will. What else?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.27,0:58:41.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nothing. Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.65,0:58:50.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,And hope to God you're lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.79,0:59:07.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.80,0:59:13.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you suddenly notice something\Nor feel something strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.84,0:59:16.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,turn right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.85,0:59:19.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just don't throw a lump of iron\Nat my head.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.21,1:00:30.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stop! Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.76,1:00:39.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Why did you do that?\N- Do what?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.30,1:00:41.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why did you stop him?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.56,1:00:44.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,| thought you did.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.31,1:01:28.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,What happened? Why did you stop me?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.14,1:01:32.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,- | didn't stop you.\N- Who did then?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.44,1:01:33.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,You?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.44,1:01:39.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,What the hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.62,1:01:44.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're a fine one, Mr. Shakespeare.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.79,1:01:47.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Afraid to advance, ashamed to retreat.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.87,1:01:51.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you order yourself to stop\Nin a false voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.54,1:01:53.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fear's sobered you up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.04,1:01:56.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What?\N- Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.13,1:01:59.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Why'd you empty my bottle?\N- | demand discipline!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.52,1:02:17.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Zone is...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.44,1:02:24.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,...a very complex maze of traps.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.08,1:02:26.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,All of them are death traps.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.54,1:02:32.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,| don't know what happens here\Nwhen humans aren't around.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.00,1:02:38.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,But as soon as humans appear,\Neverything begins to change.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.05,1:02:43.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Former traps disappear, new ones appear.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.64,1:02:47.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Safe ways become impassable.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.85,1:02:52.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,The way becomes now easy,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.81,1:02:54.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,now confused beyond words.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.44,1:03:00.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is the Zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.53,1:03:05.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,It might seem capricious.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.45,1:03:11.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,But at each moment, it's as if we construct it\Naccording to our state of mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.50,1:03:20.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,| won't hide the fact that some people\Nturned back half-way.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.42,1:03:24.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Some perished\Non the threshold of the Room.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.14,1:03:29.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,But everything that happens here\Ndepends on us.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.72,1:03:33.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,So the Zone lets the good through\Nand kills the evil?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.65,1:03:36.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,| don't Know. | don't believe that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.52,1:03:41.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,| think it lets through\Nthose who've lost all hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.49,1:03:46.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not the good or the bad, but the unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.95,1:03:52.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,But even the most unhappy will perish\Nif they don't know how to behave here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.09,1:04:05.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're lucky. The Zone warned you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.18,1:04:15.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you don't mind,\Nll wait here till you come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.44,1:04:19.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll return happy men.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.82,1:04:22.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,- That's impossible.\N- Believe me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.78,1:04:24.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've got sandwiches and a thermos.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.90,1:04:27.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,- First, you won't survive an hour.\N- And second?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.95,1:04:30.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's more,\Nnobody returns the same way.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.41,1:04:35.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,All the same, I'd prefer it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.58,1:04:38.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then we'll go back immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.67,1:04:44.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,'ll refund your money\Nminus a small sum for my trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.97,1:04:47.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sobered up, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.27,1:04:56.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right. Toss the metal nut.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.86,1:05:52.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Part Two
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.70,1:06:00.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,STALKER
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.59,1:06:06.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where are you? Come here!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.93,1:06:13.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you tired?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.28,1:06:30.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.53,1:06:39.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Judging by his tone of voice,\Nhe'll lecture us again.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.72,1:07:01.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,May everything come true.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.81,1:07:04.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,May they believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.77,1:07:09.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,And may they laugh at their own passions.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.36,1:07:14.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,For what they call passion\Nis not really the energy of the soul,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.99,1:07:17.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,but merely friction between the soul\Nand the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.66,1:07:23.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,But, above all, may they believe\Nin themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.92,1:07:27.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,and become as helpless as children.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.63,1:07:31.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,For softness is great\Nand strength is worthless.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.47,1:07:39.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,When a man is born,\Nhe ts soft and pliable.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.31,1:07:43.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,When he dies, he is strong and hard.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.69,1:07:47.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,When a tree grows, it is soft and pliable.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.15,1:07:52.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,But when it is dry and hard, it dies.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.65,1:07:57.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hardness and strength\Nare death's companions.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.49,1:08:03.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Flexibility and softness\Nare the embodiment of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.92,1:08:09.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,That which has become hard\Nshall not triumph.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.36,1:08:30.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.78,1:08:34.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,It will fit very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.86,1:08:37.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Soon we'll reach the dry tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.49,1:08:39.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Careful. Don't jinx us.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.70,1:08:44.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Are we already on our way?\N- Of course. Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.50,1:08:49.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,| thought you only wanted\Nto show us something.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.88,1:08:53.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,What about my rucksack?\N- What happened to it?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.13,1:08:57.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,| left it back there.\N| didn't know we were going.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.88,1:09:01.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It can't be helped.\N- Why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.18,1:09:03.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've got to go back.\N- It's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.60,1:09:06.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,- | can't go without my rucksack.\N- There's no going back.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.60,1:09:09.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nobody goes back\Nthe same way they came.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.65,1:09:15.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Forget your rucksack.\NWhat's in it? Diamonds?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.40,1:09:20.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll lose your way.\NThe Room will give you all you desire.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.53,1:09:23.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,It will snow you under with rucksacks.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.16,1:09:25.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is it far to this Room?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.75,1:09:30.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Straight ahead, 200 meters,\Nbut there are no direct paths.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.92,1:09:32.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.63,1:09:36.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't let doubt creep in, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.34,1:09:39.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Miracles are outside your experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.39,1:09:44.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Remember how St. Peter nearly drowned.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.94,1:09:50.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go, Writer.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.65,1:09:55.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Go where?\N- Down the ladder.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.95,1:10:09.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Professor, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.44,1:12:04.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,- This is the dry tunnel.\N- You Call this dry?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.32,1:12:11.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a local joke.\NUsually we have to swim it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.27,1:12:42.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wait. Where's the professor?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.61,1:12:45.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What?\N- The professor's lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.03,1:12:47.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Professor! Professor!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.99,1:12:50.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was following you the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.41,1:12:54.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,He must have strayed and lost his way.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.62,1:12:58.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,He didn't lose his way.\NHe went back for his rucksack.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.13,1:13:00.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now he'll never get out.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.30,1:13:07.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Shall we wait for him?\N- We can't. Things change every minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.43,1:13:09.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,The two of us must go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.54,1:13:41.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look! What"s all this?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.38,1:13:44.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,- | told you about it.\N- About what?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.01,1:13:47.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is the Zone. Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.59,1:13:50.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,We have to hurry. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.70,1:14:13.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.59,1:14:30.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,| really appreciate that you...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.59,1:14:32.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,How did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.60,1:14:40.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Most of the way, | crawled on all fours.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.94,1:14:44.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Incredible.\NHow did you manage to overtake us?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.07,1:14:47.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Overtake you?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.24,1:14:53.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,| came back here for my rucksack.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.24,1:14:56.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where did the metal nut come from?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.91,1:15:00.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,My God.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.04,1:15:03.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's a trap.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.75,1:15:11.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,Porcupine hung it here on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.14,1:15:19.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,How did the Zone let us through?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.65,1:15:27.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.32,1:15:30.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,| won't take another step until —
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.95,1:15:33.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,A good deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.95,1:15:40.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.96,1:15:43.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.76,1:15:57.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,We'll all rest here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.93,1:16:01.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,But keep away\Nfrom that metal nut in any case.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.22,1:16:05.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,| didn't think Professor would get out.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.86,1:16:13.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,| never know what sort of people\NI'm bringing in.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.15,1:16:17.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's only in here that things\Nbecome clear, when it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.66,1:16:23.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,The main thing is that the professor's\Nrucksack and spare pants are safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.25,1:16:28.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't poke your nose\Ninto another guy's drawers,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.67,1:16:30.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,if you know what | mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.46,1:16:32.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's there to understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.76,1:16:39.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't pull my leg with your binomial theorem\Nand your psychological explanations.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.14,1:16:42.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're out of favor at the institute.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.02,1:16:45.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're refused funds for an expedition.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.56,1:16:51.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,So let's fill the rucksack\Nwith manometers, shit-ometers...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.69,1:16:54.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,...Slip into the Zone illegally...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.53,1:16:58.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,...and check all the local miracles\Nwith algebra.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.74,1:17:05.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,No one in the world\Nhas any conception about the Zone,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.16,1:17:07.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,so it'll be a sensation.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.54,1:17:12.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Television,\Nyour lady fans getting hot flashes,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.09,1:17:14.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,people carrying brooms\Nas if they were laurel wreaths.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.13,1:17:21.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then our professor appears all in white\Nand declaims,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.06,1:17:25.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Mene, mene. Tekel upharsin."
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.73,1:17:32.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Naturally, everyone gapes and shouts,\N"Give him the Nobel Prize!"
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.57,1:17:41.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,You bedraggled hack writer.\NYou homegrown psychologist.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.08,1:17:47.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fit only to scribble graffiti\Nin lavatories, you talentless clod.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.04,1:17:53.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's feeble stuff. Call that an insult?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.42,1:17:57.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't know how it's done.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.67,1:18:01.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSuppose |'m after a Nobel Prize.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.59,1:18:04.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you after?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.85,1:18:09.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Want to bestow on mankind\Nthe pearls of your bought inspiration?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.10,1:18:13.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,| spit on mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.15,1:18:19.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,In all of your mankind,\Nonly one man interests me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.20,1:18:21.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,And that's me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.11,1:18:26.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Am | worth anything,\Nor am | shit like certain other people?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.95,1:18:30.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,What if you find out\Nthat's indeed what you are?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.62,1:18:35.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Know something, Einstein?\N| don't want to argue with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.97,1:18:42.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Truth is born in arguments, damn it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.06,1:18:49.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen, Chingachgook.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.35,1:18:56.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've brought so many people here.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.32,1:19:00.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not as many as | would like.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.07,1:19:03.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.99,1:19:07.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why did they come? What were they after?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.54,1:19:09.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Happiness, more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.29,1:19:13.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, but what kind of happiness?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.00,1:19:20.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,People don't like to reveal\Ntheir innermost thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.47,1:19:24.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that concerns neither you nor me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.43,1:19:27.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've been lucky.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.22,1:19:31.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,All my life, | have never seen\None happy person.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.68,1:19:33.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nor have lI.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.06,1:19:37.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,They return from the Room,\Nand | guide them back.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.57,1:19:39.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,And we never meet again.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.20,1:19:44.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wishes don't come true immediately,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.37,1:19:52.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,And you've never wanted\Nto make use of this Room?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.21,1:19:59.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm fine as | am.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.72,1:20:54.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Professor, listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.52,1:20:59.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking about inspiration you can buy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.15,1:21:09.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Suppose | return to our godforsaken city\Na genius. Understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.33,1:21:20.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,But a man writes because he's tormented,\Nunsure of himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.30,1:21:28.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,He has to keep proving his worth\Nto himself and to others.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.93,1:21:34.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,But if I'm convinced I'm a genius...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.44,1:21:39.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,...then why do | need to write?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.90,1:21:43.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's the deal?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.44,1:21:52.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Anyway, | must say we exist in order to —
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.58,1:21:55.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just leave me in peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.12,1:22:02.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let me nap a little.\N| didn't sleep all last night.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.34,1:22:06.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Keep your complexes to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.55,1:22:11.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,At any rate, all your technology —
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.22,1:22:17.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,all those blast furnaces, wheels...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.73,1:22:23.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,...and suchlike hustle and bustle
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.86,1:22:27.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,so that people can work less\Nand consume more...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.40,1:22:32.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,...they're all crutches, artificial limbs.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.20,1:22:38.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mankind exists in order to —
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.46,1:22:43.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,to create works of art.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.46,1:22:50.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,At least that's unselfish\Ncompared with all other human activities.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.18,1:22:58.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Great illusions. Images of absolute truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.27,1:23:02.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you listening to me, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.48,1:23:07.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,What unselfishness are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.69,1:23:11.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,People keep dying of hunger.\NHave you been living on the moon?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.33,1:23:25.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,And this is our intellectual aristocracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.71,1:23:29.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're unable to think in abstract terms.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.51,1:23:37.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why don't you teach me\Nthe meaning of life...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.60,1:23:42.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,...and, at the same time, how to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.60,1:23:45.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's useless.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.23,1:23:49.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,You may be a professor,\Nbut you're ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.83,1:24:44.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,'And, lo, there was a great earthquake,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.67,1:24:49.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the sun became black\Nas sackcloth of hair...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.00,1:24:53.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,...and the moon became as blood,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.30,1:24:58.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the stars of heaven\Nfell unto the earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.22,1:25:02.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,even as a fig tree casts its unripe figs
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.52,1:25:06.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,when it is shaken by a mighty wind.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.98,1:25:11.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the heavens departed as a scroll;
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.19,1:25:18.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,and every mountain and island\Nwas moved out of its place.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.91,1:25:27.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the kings of the earth\Nand the great men
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.50,1:25:33.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the rich men and the generals\Nand the mighty men...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.63,1:25:39.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,...and all free men\Nhid themselves in the dens
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.89,1:25:41.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,and in the rocks of the mountains,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.93,1:25:44.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,And they said to the mountains and rocks,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.35,1:25:50.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fall on us and hide us from\Nthe face of him that sits on the throne,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.77,1:25:53.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,and trom the wrath of the Lamb.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.73,1:25:57.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,For the great day of his wrath has come,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.07,1:26:02.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,and who shall be able to stand?"
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.42,1:29:05.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,"That same day...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.22,1:29:09.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,...two of them...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.76,1:29:17.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,...were going to a village called Emmaus.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.52,1:29:22.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,And it came to pass
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.44,1:29:29.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,that Jesus himself drew near\Nand walked with them,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.45,1:29:34.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,but they did not recognize him.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.04,1:29:38.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,'What manner of discussions are these...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.88,1:29:45.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,...that you have one to another\Nas you walk and are sad?'
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.21,1:29:46.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,And one of them, named" —
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.31,1:30:02.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,You awake?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.99,1:30:14.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,You were talking about\Nthe meaning of our life...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.33,1:30:18.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,...the unselfishness of art.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.21,1:30:24.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, take music.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.38,1:30:34.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's connected least of all with reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.18,1:30:38.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Or, if connected, then it's without ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.18,1:30:42.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's merely empty sound\Nwithout associations.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.19,1:30:52.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, music miraculously\Npenetrates your very soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.33,1:31:00.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,What chord in us\Nresponds to its harmonies...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.33,1:31:05.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,...transforming it\Ninto a source of delight,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.38,1:31:08.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,uniting us and shattering us?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.09,1:31:14.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why is all this necessary?\NAnd, above all, for whom?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.43,1:31:22.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll reply, "For no one and no reason."
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.61,1:31:28.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,No. | doubt that.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.40,1:31:34.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,For everything in the final reckoning\Nhas a meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.49,1:31:40.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,A meaning and a reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.27,1:32:12.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,You mean we go there?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.53,1:32:19.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, there's no other way.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.88,1:32:39.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's rather gloomy, eh, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.35,1:32:46.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,| don't think | should go first here.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.35,1:32:50.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Big Snake never volunteers.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.90,1:32:56.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Obviously, we'll have to draw lots.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.32,1:33:00.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here, I'd prefer some volunteer.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.29,1:33:04.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Got any matches?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.21,1:33:14.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.85,1:33:28.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,The long match goes first.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.86,1:33:33.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,The long one.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.37,1:33:43.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,This time, you were out of luck.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.18,1:34:02.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,How about throwing a metal nut?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.35,1:34:04.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of course. You're welcome to.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.09,1:34:43.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Another one?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.56,1:34:53.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.48,1:34:56.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.72,1:36:45.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hurry, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.88,1:40:57.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.64,1:41:03.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's some sort of door over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.24,1:41:21.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now it's over there.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.99,1:41:24.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Open the door and go in.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.38,1:41:37.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Me again? | should go in there?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.38,1:41:39.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,You drew your lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.18,1:41:43.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,You mustn't hang about.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.69,1:41:49.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,What have you got there?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.77,1:41:51.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,You can't go in there with a gun!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.61,1:41:55.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll be killed, and you'll doom us!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.53,1:41:57.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Remember the tanks!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.20,1:41:59.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Put it away, | beg you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.03,1:42:01.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.66,1:42:06.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,If anything happens, | can get you out.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.83,1:42:08.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,But like this —
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.33,1:42:11.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please, | beg you. And who —
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.88,1:42:16.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who will you shoot at in there?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.52,1:42:31.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go! We've very little time.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.94,1:42:37.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's water here.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.78,1:42:41.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Never mind. Hold onto the rail.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.79,1:43:31.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't go any farther.\NWait for us up there by the exit.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.35,1:43:48.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,| hope you've nothing like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.60,1:43:52.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Like what?\N- Like a pistol.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.69,1:43:55.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've an ampoule, for an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.48,1:44:00.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What kind of ampoule?\N- For protection. Poison.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.03,1:44:04.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Good God, you mean you came here to die?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.50,1:44:13.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's how it is, just in case.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.65,1:44:42.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Back!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.86,1:44:45.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Return, it's suicide!
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.24,1:44:47.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,| told you to wait at the exit.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.62,1:44:50.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.58,1:45:38.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's all because of your pipe.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.25,1:45:40.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What?\N- Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.79,1:45:43.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,You should have gone first.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.63,1:45:46.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,He took the wrong turn out of fright.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.86,1:47:36.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Another experiment.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.54,1:47:44.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Experiments, facts or truth\Nas a last resort.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.79,1:47:49.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,But there's no such things as facts,\Nespecially here.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.76,1:47:55.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,All this is someone's idiotic invention.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.39,1:47:57.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Can't you tell?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.18,1:48:03.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,You, of course,\Nwant to know whose invention.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.77,1:48:10.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,What good will it do you to know?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.11,1:48:15.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Whose conscience will be bothered by it?\NMine?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.57,1:48:20.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,| have no conscience, only nerves.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.87,1:48:24.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Some bastard abuses you, you're hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.58,1:48:28.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,A different bastard praises you, you're hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.25,1:48:33.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,You put your heart and soul\Ninto your work, and they devour you.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.39,1:48:38.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,They even devour the filth in your soul.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.68,1:48:41.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're all literate.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.06,1:48:46.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,They all have voracious appetites.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.98,1:48:55.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,They all keep crowding round —\Njournalists, editors, critics,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.41,1:48:57.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,a constant stream of women.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.57,1:49:01.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,All of them clamoring for more.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.00,1:49:07.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,What kind of writer am I...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.54,1:49:10.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,... if | detest writing?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.67,1:49:16.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,If it's torture for me,\Na painful, shameful occupation,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.80,1:49:19.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,something akin to extruding hemorrhoids.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.81,1:49:26.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,| used to think my books\Nhelped some people to become better,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.89,1:49:28.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,but nobody needs me.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.48,1:49:33.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,If | die, in a couple days,\Nthey'll find someone else to devour.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.49,1:49:39.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,| wanted to change them,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.62,1:49:44.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,but they've changed me\Nto fit their own image.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.58,1:49:54.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Once, the future was only\Na continuation of the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.46,1:49:58.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,All its changes loomed somewhere\Nbeyond the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.18,1:50:01.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,But now the future's\Na part of the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.69,1:50:11.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are they prepared for this?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.73,1:50:16.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,They don't want to know anything.\NAll they do is gobble.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.71,1:50:33.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,You certainly are lucky.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.38,1:50:39.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now you'll live to be a hundred.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.23,1:50:57.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why not forever?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.40,1:51:02.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Like the Wandering Jew.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.78,1:51:46.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,You must surely be a fine person.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.62,1:51:49.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not that | doubted it.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.20,1:51:53.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,You must have been through such agony.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.54,1:51:57.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,This pipe is the most terrible part\Nof the Zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.63,1:52:03.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,They call it the meat grinder.\NHow many people has it ground up?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.35,1:52:11.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Porcupine sent his brother through\Ninstead of himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.19,1:52:17.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was so sensitive, so gifted.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:19.98,1:52:21.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.49,1:52:27.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now the summer is passed,\Nit might never have been;
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.66,1:52:33.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,It is warm in the sun,\Nbut it isn't enough;
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.71,1:52:39.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,All that | could attain,\Nlike a five-fingered leaf,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.63,1:52:44.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,fell straight into my hand,\Nbut it isn't enough;
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.18,1:52:50.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Neither evil nor good\Nhas yet vanished in vain;
Dialogue: 0,1:52:50.64,1:52:55.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,It all burned and was light,\Nbut it isn't enough;
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.85,1:53:00.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Life has been like a shield\Nand has offered protection;
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.36,1:53:05.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,| have been very lucky,\Nbut it isn't enough;
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.53,1:53:11.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,The leaves were not burned,\Nthe boughs were not broken;
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.04,1:53:17.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,The day shines like glass,\Nbut it isn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.21,1:53:22.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fine, isn't it? That's his poem.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.17,1:53:26.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why are you evading things? "Fine" indeed!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.38,1:53:28.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,It makes me sick to look at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.55,1:53:32.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,You can't imagine how glad | am\Nthat we made it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.52,1:53:34.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your conduct was exemplary.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:36.06,1:53:39.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're fine, honest men.\NI'm proud | was right.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.65,1:53:42.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,So he's happy we got back.\NSo happy he could choke.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.86,1:53:47.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fate! Zone! So I'm a fine fellow.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.16,1:53:51.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you think | didn't see you\Noffer me two long matches?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.70,1:53:53.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You don't understand.\N- No, of course not.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.00,1:54:00.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Professor, but this louse\Nchose you as his favorite.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:00.42,1:54:02.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you going on about?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.17,1:54:05.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,He shoved me into the pipe\Nbecause I'm a second-rate person.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.67,1:54:09.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Meat grinder! What a word!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.18,1:54:15.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,What right have you to choose who lives,\Nwho goes into the meat grinder?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.10,1:54:17.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,You made the choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.44,1:54:22.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,What choice did | have —\None of two long matchsticks?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.31,1:54:24.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Forget the matches.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.65,1:54:28.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Back by the metal nut,\Nthe Zone let you through
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.57,1:54:31.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,to pass through the meat grinder.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:32.28,1:54:34.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is that for you?\N- Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.62,1:54:40.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,| never choose. You can't imagine how\Nterrible it is to make the wrong choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.50,1:54:43.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,But someone has to go first.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.05,1:54:47.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes? No, this isn't the clinic.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:49.26,1:54:52.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Someone has to go first!\NHow would you like it?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.98,1:55:01.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't touch it!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.17,1:55:25.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yes?\N- Laboratory Nine, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.59,1:55:28.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,One minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.47,1:55:35.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,/m listening.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.68,1:55:38.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,- | hope | haven't disturbed you.\N- What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.35,1:55:42.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just a few words.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.27,1:55:47.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,You hid it. | found it\Nin the old building, Bunker 4.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.61,1:55:53.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you listening?\N-// inform the security service.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.28,1:55:58.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go on! Inform on me, write a denunciation.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.95,1:56:03.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Set my colleagues against me.\NBut you're late.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:03.42,1:56:06.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm just two steps away\Nfrom the place itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.96,1:56:09.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:09.88,1:56:12.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,You realize\Nthis finishes you as a scientist?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.55,1:56:13.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,So be happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.88,1:56:16.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you realize what happens if you dare?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.35,1:56:21.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Trying to scare me again?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.23,1:56:29.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, all my life I've been scared.\NEven of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:29.23,1:56:32.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't scare me anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.90,1:56:36.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,My God, youre not even Herostratus.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.41,1:56:43.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,You just wanted to trip me up because,\N20 years ago, | slept with your wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:43.37,1:56:47.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've finally managed\Nto settle the score.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:47.75,1:56:52.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go on, do your dirty work.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.22,1:56:54.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't dare hang up on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:56.72,1:56:59.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Prison isnt the worst thing\Nthat awaits you.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.06,1:57:03.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,You'll never forgive yourself for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.27,1:57:07.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,/ can see you hanging from your belt\Nover a prison /atrine.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.90,1:57:14.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you up to, Professor?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.91,1:57:20.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Imagine what will happen\Nwhen everyone believes in this Room...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:22.12,1:57:25.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,... and when they all come hurrying here.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:26.21,1:57:31.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's only a question of time.\NNot today, but tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.88,1:57:33.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,And in the thousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.96,1:57:37.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,All these would-be emperors,\Ngrand inquisitors,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:37.30,1:57:39.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,fuhrers of all shades.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:39.14,1:57:43.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,The so-called saviors of mankind!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.39,1:57:47.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,And not for money or inspiration,\Nbut to remake the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:48.06,1:57:52.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'll never bring that sort here.\N- What do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.15,1:57:56.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're not the only stalker in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.90,1:58:02.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,No stalker Knows what ideas the people\Nyou bring here take away with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.41,1:58:06.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,The number of motiveless crimes\Nis growing.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.41,1:58:08.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Isn't that your work?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.33,1:58:10.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,What about the military coups?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.46,1:58:15.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,The mafia in the governments,\Ncouldn't they be your clients?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:15.76,1:58:17.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,What about the lasers,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:17.68,1:58:24.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,the deadly bacteria hidden away\Nin vaults for the time being?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:24.56,1:58:27.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stop this sociological drivel!
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.85,1:58:29.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you really believe\Nin these fairy tales?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.02,1:58:34.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not in the good ones,\Nbut in the terrifying ones, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:34.86,1:58:36.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just stop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:37.03,1:58:43.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,No single individual can have\Nenough hatred or love
Dialogue: 0,1:58:43.16,1:58:45.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,to spread over all mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:47.12,1:58:52.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,You desire money, a woman.\NOr you want your boss to get run over.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:53.04,1:58:55.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's neither here nor there.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:55.38,1:58:58.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,But world domination, a just society,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:58.51,1:59:00.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,the kingdom of heaven on earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.76,1:59:05.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Those aren't desires,\Nbut an ideology, actions, concepts.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:07.14,1:59:12.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Subconscious compassion\Ncannot yet be realized
Dialogue: 0,1:59:12.52,1:59:15.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,as a common instinctive desire.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:16.03,1:59:20.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,You can't be happy at the expense\Nof others' unhappiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:21.16,1:59:27.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,| see you've decided to smash humanity\Nwith some inconceivable boon.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:29.37,1:59:31.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yet I'm completely calm.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:31.96,1:59:35.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not worried about you or myself\Nor mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.42,1:59:39.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nothing will come of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.97,1:59:44.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,At best,\Nyou'll receive your Nobel Prize...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:46.35,1:59:51.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,...or more probably something\Nquite inconceivable
Dialogue: 0,1:59:51.60,1:59:54.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,which you haven't even thought about.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:54.44,1:59:56.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,A telephone.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:57.73,2:00:02.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,You dream of one thing\Nand get something quite different.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:04.07,2:00:05.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:20.09,2:00:23.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,A telephone, electricity.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:27.64,2:00:30.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:31.27,2:00:34.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,This sort isn't prescribed anymore.\NWhere did they come from?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:39.44,2:00:41.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shall we go there?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:42.28,2:00:46.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,It'll soon be evening,\Ntoo dark to get back.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:53.87,2:00:56.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,By the way,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:56.58,2:01:01.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,| can see that all this poetry reciting\Nand walking around
Dialogue: 0,2:01:01.38,2:01:05.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,is a new, original way of apologizing.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:05.26,2:01:06.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,| understand you.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:08.89,2:01:12.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,A difficult childhood environment.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:12.56,2:01:14.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,But don't fool yourself.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:17.31,2:01:19.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,| don't forgive you.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:19.90,2:01:22.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't. Please.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:14.79,2:02:17.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Professor, come here.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:51.62,2:02:55.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just a moment. No need to rush.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:55.45,2:02:57.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not rushing anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:48.34,2:03:50.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't get angry.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:53.51,2:03:55.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,But | have to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:02.60,2:04:07.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're now standing at the threshold.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:15.28,2:04:20.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is the most important moment...\Nin your life.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:23.54,2:04:25.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,You must know that...
Dialogue: 0,2:04:27.21,2:04:32.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,... your most cherished desire\Nwill come true here.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:33.93,2:04:39.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your sincerest wish, the desire\Nthat has made you suffer most.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:08.96,2:05:10.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's no need to speak.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:14.34,2:05:20.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,You must only... concentrate
Dialogue: 0,2:05:20.18,2:05:23.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,and recall all your past life.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:26.35,2:05:31.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,When a man thinks of the past,\Nhe becomes kinder.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:32.69,2:05:34.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,But the main thing —
Dialogue: 0,2:06:08.10,2:06:09.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,The main thing is...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:14.36,2:06:15.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,... you must believe.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:25.33,2:06:26.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now go.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:32.84,2:06:34.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who wants to go first?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:39.68,2:06:41.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:43.01,2:06:46.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Me? No, | don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:47.18,2:06:49.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,| Know it's not easy.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:49.23,2:06:52.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,But don't worry. That will soon pass.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:53.52,2:06:57.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure... that it will.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:00.07,2:07:03.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Firstly, if | begin to recall my life...
Dialogue: 0,2:07:05.29,2:07:07.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,...| shall hardly become kinder.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:09.04,2:07:13.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,And then, can't you see\Nhow shameful all this is?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:31.73,2:07:33.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,To humiliate yourself.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:34.56,2:07:37.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,To snivel and to pray.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:37.90,2:07:39.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's bad about praying?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:42.11,2:07:44.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's your pride speaking.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:46.03,2:07:51.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Relax. You're just not ready.\NThat happens.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:54.00,2:07:55.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you'll go first?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:03.93,2:08:05.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:16.06,2:08:21.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Voila! Here we have\Nthe professor's new invention.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:22.15,2:08:26.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,A device for testing the human soul.\NA soul meter.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:26.78,2:08:29.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's just a bomb.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:29.58,2:08:30.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:32.79,2:08:35.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You're joking.\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:37.84,2:08:40.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's just a 20-kiloton bomb.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:41.51,2:08:42.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,What for?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:53.60,2:08:57.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,| assembled it with some friends.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:59.36,2:09:03.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,With some former colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:07.49,2:09:10.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,This place, evidently,\Nwon't bring anyone happiness.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:15.50,2:09:20.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,And if it falls into evil hands...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:22.46,2:09:24.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,However, | really don't know now.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:26.68,2:09:28.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Once we had the idea...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:31.47,2:09:34.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,...that the Zone should not be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:35.52,2:09:41.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Even if it was a miracle,\Nit was a part of nature.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:41.78,2:09:44.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,And in a certain sense, it means hope.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:46.66,2:09:51.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,They hid this bomb, but I've found it.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:51.41,2:09:54.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's an old building, Bunker 4.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:59.29,2:10:02.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Obviously there must be a principle —
Dialogue: 0,2:10:04.30,2:10:06.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,never to perform irreversible actions.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:07.22,2:10:09.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,| understand that. I'm no maniac.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:13.97,2:10:19.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,But as long as this canker\Nis Open to any scoundrel...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:22.15,2:10:23.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,...there can be no rest.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:31.78,2:10:34.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Maybe something inside us won't permit it?
Dialogue: 0,2:10:41.42,2:10:44.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Poor guy, he's made himself a problem.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:08.15,2:11:09.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:24.09,2:11:25.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give it to me!
Dialogue: 0,2:11:30.59,2:11:32.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're an intelligent man.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:40.23,2:11:43.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What's that for?\N- You hypocritical louse!
Dialogue: 0,2:11:45.65,2:11:51.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why — Why are you doing this to me?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:51.45,2:11:55.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,He wants to destroy your hope.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:18.18,2:12:21.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's nothing else left\Nto people on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:22.69,2:12:29.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is the only place to come to\Nwhen all hope is gone.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:32.53,2:12:37.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have to come here.\NThen why destroy hope?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:38.54,2:12:40.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,2:12:42.75,2:12:46.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,| see through you.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:46.38,2:12:49.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't give a damn about others.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:49.55,2:12:55.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,You earn your money from our... misery.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:55.39,2:12:58.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's not even the money. You enjoy this.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:58.85,2:13:00.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here you're czar and God.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:00.89,2:13:05.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,You louse, you decide\Nwho's to die and who's to live.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:05.35,2:13:07.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,He chooses, he decides.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:09.19,2:13:13.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,| Know why the stalker himself\Nnever enters the Room.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:13.74,2:13:19.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,What for?\NYou're drunk with power out here.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:19.24,2:13:21.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,With mystery! With authority!
Dialogue: 0,2:13:21.37,2:13:24.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's not true. You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:29.92,2:13:32.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,A stalker is forbidden to enter the Room.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:32.51,2:13:36.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Especially for his own selfish reasons.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:37.26,2:13:39.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Remember Porcupine.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:41.89,2:13:44.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm a louse.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:44.14,2:13:47.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've never achieved anything,\Nand | can't do anything here.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:49.90,2:13:52.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,| have nothing to give my wife.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:53.40,2:13:58.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,| can't have any friends,\Nbut don't deprive me of what's mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:58.24,2:14:01.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,They took everything from me\Nbehind the barbed wire.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:06.12,2:14:08.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Everything | have is here.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:08.83,2:14:11.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Here, in the Zone.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:12.88,2:14:17.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,My happiness, my freedom, dignity.\NThey're all here.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:19.80,2:14:23.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,The people | bring are unhappy like me.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:23.68,2:14:27.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,They've nothing left to hope for.\NNobody can help them.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:28.73,2:14:34.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,But | can — a louse.\NA louse can help them!
Dialogue: 0,2:14:37.36,2:14:39.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,| weep for joy because | can help them.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:42.08,2:14:43.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,| ask for nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:06.31,2:15:08.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,| don't know. Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:09.10,2:15:11.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Anyway, forgive me, but —
Dialogue: 0,2:15:12.81,2:15:14.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're simply one of God's fools.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:17.03,2:15:19.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've no conception\Nof what's happening here.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:23.99,2:15:27.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why do you think Porcupine\Nhanged himself?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:27.54,2:15:34.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,He came to the Zone for profit,\Nand his brother died for money.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:34.21,2:15:38.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,| understand that,\Nbut why did he hang himself?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:38.21,2:15:42.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why didn't he come back?\NNot for money, but for his brother.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:43.72,2:15:45.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is that how he repented?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:45.56,2:15:49.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,He wanted to.\NBut within a few days, he hanged himself.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:50.06,2:15:56.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,He realized that it is one's\Nmost secret desire that is granted here.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:04.57,2:16:06.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you yelling about?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:15.17,2:16:19.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,What comes true here is that which\Nreflects the essence of your nature.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:19.92,2:16:23.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,It is within you. It governs you.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:23.09,2:16:26.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yet you are ignorant of it.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:26.68,2:16:31.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've understood nothing.\NGreed didn't do Porcupine in.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:31.43,2:16:35.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,He crawled on his knees\Nto plead for his brother,
Dialogue: 0,2:16:35.23,2:16:37.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,but he got a pile of money.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:37.57,2:16:40.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,He couldn't get anything else.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:41.15,2:16:44.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Porcupine was given the essence\Nof his true nature.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:44.78,2:16:49.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Conscience and soul-searching\Nwere all invented by the mind.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:49.79,2:16:51.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,When he realized all that,\Nhe hanged himself.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:56.83,2:16:58.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,| won't go into your Room.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:00.67,2:17:05.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,| don't want to pour the filth in my soul\Nonto anyone's head —
Dialogue: 0,2:17:06.01,2:17:08.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,even yours —
Dialogue: 0,2:17:08.39,2:17:10.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,and then hang myself as Porcupine did.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:12.14,2:17:17.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Better to stay grunting\Nin my stinking private villa.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:19.61,2:17:25.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're a bad judge of human nature
Dialogue: 0,2:17:25.28,2:17:27.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,if you bring people like me into the Zone.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:35.87,2:17:43.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,How did you learn\Nthat this miracle actually exists?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:44.72,2:17:49.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who told you that desires\Nreally come true here?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:51.72,2:17:56.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you know one man\Nwho was made happy here?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:57.65,2:17:59.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Perhaps Porcupine?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:04.49,2:18:09.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,And who told you about the Zone,
Dialogue: 0,2:18:09.20,2:18:12.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,about Porcupine, about this Room?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:14.37,2:18:15.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,He did.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:20.56,2:19:22.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,| don't understand anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:24.44,2:19:26.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's the sense in coming here?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:50.44,2:20:51.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's so still.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:53.53,2:20:55.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Can you hear it?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:00.37,2:21:03.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Suppose | chuck it all in...
Dialogue: 0,2:21:05.37,2:21:09.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,...get my wife and Monkey\Nand come here to live...
Dialogue: 0,2:21:13.55,2:21:14.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,... forever.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:17.39,2:21:18.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's nobody here.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:20.22,2:21:22.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,No one will hurt them.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:37.15,2:25:38.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,You came back.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:44.90,2:25:46.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where did the dog come from?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:48.16,2:25:52.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,It tagged along. Don't chase it away.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:09.51,2:26:12.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:13.60,2:26:15.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Monkey's waiting.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:19.23,2:26:20.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are we going?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:35.00,2:26:37.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Does anybody want a dog?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:40.38,2:26:42.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've got five already.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:52.89,2:26:55.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you like dogs?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:55.98,2:26:57.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:57.56,2:26:58.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:04.78,2:27:07.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,All right, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:10.13,2:30:12.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you only knew how tired | am.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:14.17,2:30:15.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Only God knows.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:18.05,2:30:21.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,They still call themselves\Nthe intelligentsia.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:21.22,2:30:24.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Writers! Scientists!\N- Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:24.89,2:30:27.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,They don't believe in anything.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:27.52,2:30:32.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Their capacity for faith has atrophied —
Dialogue: 0,2:30:32.61,2:30:34.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Calm yourself.\N- ...through lack of use.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:36.15,2:30:40.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Stop it. Come, lie down. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:40.20,2:30:44.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's damp. You can't stay here.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:48.54,2:30:50.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Take it off.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:01.32,2:32:03.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,My God, what kind people are they?
Dialogue: 0,2:32:03.32,2:32:07.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Calm down. It isn't their fault.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:07.70,2:32:10.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,They should be pitied, not abused.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:10.50,2:32:12.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Their eyes are blank.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:25.72,2:32:29.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're thinking\Nhow not to sell themselves cheap,
Dialogue: 0,2:32:29.35,2:32:34.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,how to get paid\Nfor every breath they take.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:38.11,2:32:42.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,They know they were born\Nto "be someone,' to be an elite!
Dialogue: 0,2:32:45.53,2:32:47.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,They say, "You live but once."
Dialogue: 0,2:32:49.58,2:32:52.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,How can such people believe\Nin anything at all?
Dialogue: 0,2:32:53.71,2:32:55.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Relax now.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:55.50,2:32:59.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Try to get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:00.63,2:33:02.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:05.59,2:33:09.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nobody believes. Not only those two.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:10.60,2:33:11.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:12.43,2:33:14.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who shall | take there?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:18.44,2:33:20.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:20.86,2:33:22.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,The most terrible thing...
Dialogue: 0,2:33:24.91,2:33:31.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,...1S that nobody needs that Room\Nand all my efforts are in vain.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:32.45,2:33:35.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why do you say that? Don't.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:41.80,2:33:43.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll never go there again with anyone.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:47.18,2:33:51.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you want, I'll go there with you.\NDo you want that?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:54.06,2:33:56.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you think I've nothing to ask for?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:01.61,2:34:02.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:06.66,2:34:09.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,You mustn't.\N- Why?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:12.33,2:34:13.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:18.71,2:34:22.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,What if you fail, too?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:58.71,2:35:01.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know, Mama was very opposed to it.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:03.88,2:35:08.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've probably already guessed\Nthat he's one of God's fools.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:11.47,2:35:13.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Everyone around here used to laugh at him.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:13.89,2:35:16.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was such a wretched muddler.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:19.31,2:35:21.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mama used to Say,
Dialogue: 0,2:35:21.65,2:35:26.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,"He's a stalker, a marked man,\Nan eternal jailbird.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:26.11,2:35:28.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Remember the kind of children\Nstalkers have."
Dialogue: 0,2:35:29.07,2:35:31.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,| didn't even argue.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:34.87,2:35:37.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,| Knew all about it —
Dialogue: 0,2:35:37.33,2:35:43.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,that he was a marked man, a jailbird,\Nabout the kids.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:46.96,2:35:49.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Only what could | do?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:49.09,2:35:51.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,| was sure I'd be happy with him.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:54.39,2:35:56.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,| knew there'd be a lot of sorrow.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:58.18,2:36:03.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I'd rather know\Nbittersweet happiness...
Dialogue: 0,2:36:04.77,2:36:06.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,... than a gray, uneventtul life.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:11.61,2:36:15.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Perhaps | invented all this later.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:24.75,2:36:29.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,But when he came up to me and said,\N"Come with me," | went.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:31.30,2:36:34.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I've never regretted it.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:37.81,2:36:39.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:41.89,2:36:45.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,There was a lot of grief
Dialogue: 0,2:36:45.11,2:36:47.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,and fear and pain.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:47.52,2:36:51.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I've never regretted it\Nnor envied anyone.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:53.24,2:36:55.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's just fate.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:56.78,2:36:59.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's life. It's us.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:04.67,2:37:08.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,And if there were no sorrow in our lives,\Nit wouldn't be better.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:10.13,2:37:11.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,It would be worse.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:14.43,2:37:19.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because then\Nthere would be no happiness either.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:21.77,2:37:24.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,And there'd be no hope.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:27.48,2:37:28.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,SO...
Dialogue: 0,2:38:15.15,2:38:18.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,/ love those eyes of yours, my friend,
Dialogue: 0,2:38:18.87,2:38:23.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Their sparkling, tlashing, tlery wonder;
Dialogue: 0,2:38:23.58,2:38:27.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,When suddenly those lids ascend,
Dialogue: 0,2:38:27.42,2:38:30.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then lightning rips the sky asunder,
Dialogue: 0,2:38:30.92,2:38:35.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,You swiftly glance, and there's an end,
Dialogue: 0,2:38:35.09,2:38:38.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's greater charm, though, to admire
Dialogue: 0,2:38:38.76,2:38:42.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,When lowered are those eyes divine
Dialogue: 0,2:38:42.31,2:38:45.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,In moments kissed by passion's fire;
Dialogue: 0,2:38:45.93,2:38:50.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,When through the downcast lashes shine
Dialogue: 0,2:38:50.11,2:38:56.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,The smoldering embers of desire...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.27,0:00:32.06,FR,,0,0,0,,MOSFILM
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.07,0:00:37.49,FR,,0,0,0,,Deuxième Union Artistique
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.26,0:00:56.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Alissa Freindlich
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.39,0:01:03.69,FR,,0,0,0,,Alexandre Kaïdanovski
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.10,0:01:10.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Anatoli Solonitsyne
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.36,0:01:16.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Nicolaï Grinko
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.57,0:01:21.24,FR,,0,0,0,,dans
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.54,0:01:28.50,FR,,0,0,0,,STALKER
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.71,0:01:34.80,FR,,0,0,0,,Scénario\Nd'Arcadi et Boris Strougatski
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.97,0:01:39.18,FR,,0,0,0,,inspiré de la nouvelle\N{\i1}Pique-nique au bord du chemin{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:49.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Réalisation\NAndreï Tarkovski
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.94,0:01:56.82,FR,,0,0,0,,Directeur de la photographie\NAlexandre Kniajinski
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.24,0:02:03.79,FR,,0,0,0,,Décors\NAndreï Tarkovski
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.16,0:02:10.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Musique\NEdouard Artemiev
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.75,0:02:15.63,FR,,0,0,0,,Assistant réalisateur\NL. Tarkovskaïa
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.05,0:02:22.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Poèmes de\NFiodor Tiouttchev et Arseni Tarkovski
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.97,0:02:25.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Son\NV. Charoune
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.64,0:02:29.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Orchestre sous la direction de\NE. Khatchatourian
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.94,0:02:32.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Maquillage\NV. Lvova
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.19,0:02:35.94,FR,,0,0,0,,Chef monteur\NL. Feïguinova
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.11,0:02:38.03,FR,,0,0,0,,Costumes\NN. Fomina
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.83,0:03:38.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Directrice de production\NAlexandra Démidova
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.51,0:03:45.06,FR,,0,0,0,,STALKER
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.01,0:03:50.85,FR,,0,0,0,,Qu'est-ce que c'était ?\NLa chute d'une météorite ?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.06,0:03:54.19,FR,,0,0,0,,La visite d'habitants\Nde l'abîme cosmique ?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.40,0:03:57.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Quoi qu'il en soit,\Ndans notre petit pays
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.61,0:04:01.32,FR,,0,0,0,,s'était produit le miracle\Ndes miracles : la ZONE.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.53,0:04:05.08,FR,,0,0,0,,On y envoya des troupes.\NElles ne revinrent pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.28,0:04:08.24,FR,,0,0,0,,On encercla la Zone\Nde cordons de police.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.45,0:04:12.33,FR,,0,0,0,,On fit bien, je pense...\NEnfin, je n'en sais rien...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.54,0:04:16.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Extrait de l'interview\Ndu professeur Wolles, prix Nobel,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.92,0:04:19.30,FR,,0,0,0,,accordée à l'envoyé de la RAI.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.82,0:10:21.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi as-tu pris ma montre ?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.00,0:10:26.92,FR,,0,0,0,,Où vas-tu ? Dis-le-moi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.96,0:10:32.92,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu m'avais pourtant juré.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.67,0:10:35.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Et je t'ai cru.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.89,0:10:42.73,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu ne veux pas penser à toi,\Nmais nous ?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.22,0:10:46.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Pense à ton enfant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.39,0:10:50.85,FR,,0,0,0,,Elle n'est pas encore\Nhabituée à toi
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.02,0:10:52.52,FR,,0,0,0,,et tu repars déjà.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.74,0:11:00.62,FR,,0,0,0,,Je suis devenue vieille,\Ntu m'as achevée.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.11,0:11:03.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Chut ! Tu vas réveiller Ouistiti.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:09.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne peux pas t'attendre\Néternellement, j'en mourrai.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.14,0:11:25.31,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu avais l'intention de travailler.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:30.02,FR,,0,0,0,,On t'avait promis\Nun travail décent et honorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.90,0:11:35.44,FR,,0,0,0,,Je rentrerai bientôt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.40,0:11:38.90,FR,,0,0,0,,En prison, oui !
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.53,0:11:42.33,FR,,0,0,0,,Cette fois tu écoperas\Nde dix ans et non cinq.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.53,0:11:44.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Pendant lesquels tu n'auras rien.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.91,0:11:46.87,FR,,0,0,0,,Plus de Zone, rien.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.70,0:11:51.50,FR,,0,0,0,,Et moi, pendant ces dix ans,\Nje crèverai.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.54,0:11:55.04,FR,,0,0,0,,En prison...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.59,0:11:57.51,FR,,0,0,0,,Je suis partout en prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.05,0:12:02.43,FR,,0,0,0,,- Laisse-moi.\N- Non.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.89,0:12:05.52,FR,,0,0,0,,- Laisse-moi.\N- Non.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.69,0:12:17.02,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors fous le camp !
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.15,0:12:19.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Puisses-tu y pourrir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.24,0:12:25.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Maudit soit le jour\Noù je t'ai rencontré, salaud !
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.16,0:12:30.04,FR,,0,0,0,,Dieu t'a maudit en te donnant\Nun enfant comme le tien.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.95,0:12:34.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Et il m'a maudite à cause de toi.\NSalaud !
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.50,0:13:24.25,FR,,0,0,0,,Ma chère, le monde\Nest désespérément ennuyeux.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.55,0:13:28.76,FR,,0,0,0,,Donc la télépathie, les revenants,\Nles soucoupes volantes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.97,0:13:31.22,FR,,0,0,0,,ne peuvent exister.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.81,0:13:34.48,FR,,0,0,0,,Le monde est régi\Npar des lois de plomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.64,0:13:36.60,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est d'un ennui insupportable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.81,0:13:41.44,FR,,0,0,0,,Hélas, on ne peut enfreindre ces lois.\NElles sont inviolables.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.49,0:13:48.04,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne comptez pas sur les soucoupes\Nvolantes, ce serait trop intéressant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.24,0:13:51.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Et le triangle des Bermudes ?\NVous ne contestez pas...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.91,0:13:53.33,FR,,0,0,0,,Si, je le conteste.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.87,0:13:56.16,FR,,0,0,0,,Il n'y a pas de triangle des Bermudes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.37,0:14:01.04,FR,,0,0,0,,Il y a le triangle ABC\Nqui est égal au triangle A'B'C'.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.88,0:14:05.72,FR,,0,0,0,,Ressentez-vous l'ennui mortel\Nqu'implique cette affirmation ?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.43,0:14:09.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Au Moyen Âge par contre,\Nc'était intéressant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.60,0:14:11.69,FR,,0,0,0,,Dans chaque maison, un génie du foyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.31,0:14:13.94,FR,,0,0,0,,dans chaque église, Dieu.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.14,0:14:15.52,FR,,0,0,0,,Les gens étaient jeunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.73,0:14:18.36,FR,,0,0,0,,À présent, un homme sur quatre\Nest un vieux.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.56,0:14:21.19,FR,,0,0,0,,Quel ennui, mon ange.\NDieu, quel ennui.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.52,0:14:23.27,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais vous disiez vous-même
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.48,0:14:26.69,FR,,0,0,0,,que la Zone est l'œuvre\Nd'une super-civilisation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.90,0:14:28.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Aussi ennuyeuse sans doute.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.28,0:14:31.99,FR,,0,0,0,,Avec des lois, des triangles,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.20,0:14:35.70,FR,,0,0,0,,sans génies du foyer\Net sans Dieu bien sûr.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.29,0:14:41.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Car s'il y a un Dieu, alors\Nce fameux triangle...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:44.96,FR,,0,0,0,,je n'en sais rien.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.76,0:14:51.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Ah, c'est pour moi, parfait.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.26,0:14:52.72,FR,,0,0,0,,Adieu, chère amie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.14,0:14:54.31,FR,,0,0,0,,Excusez-moi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.02,0:14:58.23,FR,,0,0,0,,Cette dame accepte de venir\Navec nous dans la Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.44,0:15:01.61,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est une femme courageuse.\NElle s'appelle...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.48,0:15:04.73,FR,,0,0,0,,Pardon, vous vous appelez...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.94,0:15:07.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Ainsi, vous êtes vraiment un Stalker ?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.16,0:15:16.16,FR,,0,0,0,,Je vais tout vous expliquer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:26.01,FR,,0,0,0,,Partez.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.72,0:15:35.81,FR,,0,0,0,,Crétin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.56,0:15:42.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous vous êtes quand même saoulé.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.94,0:15:45.23,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi ? Que voulez-vous dire ?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.65,0:15:49.15,FR,,0,0,0,,J'ai juste bu un coup,\Ncomme le fait la moitié des gens.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.36,0:15:53.28,FR,,0,0,0,,L'autre moitié se saoule, oui.\NFemmes et enfants compris.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.99,0:15:55.83,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi, j'ai juste bu un coup.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.60,0:16:20.56,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est plein de flotte ici.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.16,0:16:36.62,FR,,0,0,0,,Prenez quelque chose,\Nil y a le temps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.04,0:16:42.38,FR,,0,0,0,,Un petit verre\Navant de prendre la route ?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.33,0:16:45.83,FR,,0,0,0,,Qu'en dites-vous ?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.31,0:17:01.65,FR,,0,0,0,,Rangez-moi ça.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.14,0:17:04.89,FR,,0,0,0,,Je vois. Régime sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.10,0:17:07.52,FR,,0,0,0,,"L'alcoolisme, fléau des peuples."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.69,0:17:09.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Eh bien, buvons de la bière.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.24,0:17:13.87,FR,,0,0,0,,Il vient avec nous ?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.82,0:17:18.24,FR,,0,0,0,,Il dessaoulera.\NLui aussi doit y aller.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.42,0:17:28.80,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors, vous êtes vraiment professeur ?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.75,0:17:31.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Si vous voulez.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.34,0:17:34.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Permettez alors que je me présente.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.01,0:17:37.81,FR,,0,0,0,,- Je m'appelle...\N- Vous vous appelez l'Écrivain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.43,0:17:40.81,FR,,0,0,0,,Et moi, comment je m'appelle ?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.01,0:17:43.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous, vous êtes le Professeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.94,0:17:47.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Très bien, je suis écrivain,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.60,0:17:50.85,FR,,0,0,0,,alors naturellement,\Ntout le monde me nomme ainsi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.19,0:17:52.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Et quel est votre sujet ?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.11,0:17:54.61,FR,,0,0,0,,Les lecteurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.03,0:17:57.41,FR,,0,0,0,,Il n'y a pas d'autre sujet valable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.61,0:18:00.86,FR,,0,0,0,,Écrire est inutile.\NIl n'y a pas de bons sujets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.83,0:18:05.67,FR,,0,0,0,,Et vous, vous êtes chimiste ?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.96,0:18:08.50,FR,,0,0,0,,Plutôt physicien.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.83,0:18:12.67,FR,,0,0,0,,Ennuyeux aussi, j'imagine.\NLa recherche de la vérité...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.46,0:18:16.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Elle se cache\Net vous la cherchez partout.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.59,0:18:18.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous creusez ici ou là.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.34,0:18:22.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Ici, vous découvrez que le noyau\Nse compose de protons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.43,0:18:24.27,FR,,0,0,0,,Là, ô merveille,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.64,0:18:28.52,FR,,0,0,0,,le triangle ABC est égal\Nau triangle A'B'C'.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.40,0:18:31.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Pour moi, c'est différent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.73,0:18:35.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Cette vérité,\Npendant que je la déterre,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.11,0:18:38.20,FR,,0,0,0,,il lui arrive quelque chose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.41,0:18:40.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Je pensais déterrer la vérité,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.95,0:18:44.83,FR,,0,0,0,,mais entre-temps cela devient\Nun tas de... vous savez quoi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.00,0:18:52.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Pour vous tout va bien.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.25,0:18:56.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Regardez ce pot antique\Ndans un musée.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.63,0:18:59.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Jadis, on y jetait des ordures.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.55,0:19:03.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Aujourd'hui, il suscite\Nl'admiration générale
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.60,0:19:07.27,FR,,0,0,0,,par la sobriété de son dessin\Net sa forme incomparable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.48,0:19:09.44,FR,,0,0,0,,Tout le monde est en extase.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.56,0:19:14.11,FR,,0,0,0,,Puis, on découvre soudain\Nqu'il n'a rien d'antique,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.90,0:19:19.07,FR,,0,0,0,,qu'il a été présenté aux archéologues\Npar quelque farceur.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.95,0:19:21.33,FR,,0,0,0,,Histoire de rire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.49,0:19:24.20,FR,,0,0,0,,Comme par hasard,\Nplus personne ne s'extasie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.83,0:19:26.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Fins connaisseurs !
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.37,0:19:28.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous pensez à ça tout le temps ?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.92,0:19:32.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Dieu m'en garde.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.13,0:19:35.59,FR,,0,0,0,,Je pense peu, cela m'est néfaste.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.05,0:19:39.14,FR,,0,0,0,,Il est impossible d'écrire\Nen pensant au succès
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.34,0:19:41.01,FR,,0,0,0,,ou au contraire, à l'échec.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.22,0:19:42.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Bien sûr.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.51,0:19:46.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais si on ne lit pas mes livres\Ndans cent ans,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.43,0:19:48.93,FR,,0,0,0,,pourquoi diable écrire, alors ?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.60,0:19:55.61,FR,,0,0,0,,Professeur, pourquoi vous être mêlé\Nà cette histoire ?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:19:57.95,FR,,0,0,0,,Qu'attendez-vous de la Zone ?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.07,0:20:03.20,FR,,0,0,0,,D'une certaine façon,\Nje suis chercheur.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.33,0:20:07.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Et vous, qu'en attendez-vous ?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.62,0:20:10.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Un écrivain à la mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.42,0:20:14.26,FR,,0,0,0,,Les femmes doivent se pendre\Nà votre cou.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.46,0:20:19.30,FR,,0,0,0,,J'ai perdu l'inspiration, Professeur.\NAlors je vais mendier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.84,0:20:23.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment ça ? Votre plume s'est tarie ?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.30,0:20:24.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Quoi ?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.64,0:20:27.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Oui, peut-être...\NOn peut dire ça.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.27,0:20:30.44,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous entendez ?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.60,0:20:33.02,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est notre train.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.99,0:20:43.16,FR,,0,0,0,,- Le toit de la voiture est relevé ?\N- Oui, oui.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.04,0:20:57.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Luther ?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.55,0:21:03.47,FR,,0,0,0,,Si je ne reviens pas,\Npasse voir ma femme.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.40,0:21:21.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Mince, j'ai oublié\Nd'acheter des cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.90,0:21:24.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne revenez pas sur vos pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.99,0:21:28.24,FR,,0,0,0,,- Pourquoi ?\N- Il ne faut pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.78,0:21:31.49,FR,,0,0,0,,- Vous êtes tous les mêmes.\N- C'est-à-dire ?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.16,0:21:34.50,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous croyez à toutes ces sornettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.67,0:21:38.17,FR,,0,0,0,,J'économise celles que j'ai, alors.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.51,0:21:43.68,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous êtes vraiment chercheur ?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.90,0:23:22.03,FR,,0,0,0,,Couchez-vous !
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.19,0:23:27.48,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne bougez pas !
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.22,0:24:00.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Regardez s'il y a quelqu'un.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.82,0:24:07.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Allons, pressez-vous !
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.70,0:24:15.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Il n'y a personne.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.62,0:24:17.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Allez vers l'autre sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.56,0:24:46.85,FR,,0,0,0,,Il y a encore quelqu'un, l'Écrivain.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.28,0:27:00.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Faites le guet, s'il vous plaît.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.05,0:27:58.18,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous n'avez pas oublié le jerrycan ?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.63,0:28:00.51,FR,,0,0,0,,Il est là, plein.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.15,0:28:17.24,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce que je vous disais tout à l'heure,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.78,0:28:19.41,FR,,0,0,0,,c'était des bêtises.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.49,0:28:22.87,FR,,0,0,0,,Je me foutais de l'inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.41,0:28:24.62,FR,,0,0,0,,Et ensuite...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.95,0:28:29.87,FR,,0,0,0,,D'ailleurs, comment nommer\Nce que je veux ?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.58,0:28:34.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Et comment savoir qu'en réalité,\Nje ne veux pas ce que je veux ?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.92,0:28:39.51,FR,,0,0,0,,Ou que je ne veux vraiment pas\Nce que je ne veux pas ?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.55,0:28:42.59,FR,,0,0,0,,Ces choses sont insaisissables.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.76,0:28:46.64,FR,,0,0,0,,Il suffit de les nommer\Net leur sens disparaît et se dissout
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.81,0:28:50.11,FR,,0,0,0,,comme une méduse au soleil.\NVous avez déjà vu ça ?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.10,0:28:54.69,FR,,0,0,0,,Ma conscience veut que le monde entier\Ndevienne végétarien,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.90,0:28:58.57,FR,,0,0,0,,mais mon inconscient se languit\Nd'un beau morceau de viande.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.19,0:29:01.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Qu'est-ce que je veux, moi ?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.57,0:29:03.53,FR,,0,0,0,,Dites-moi ?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.70,0:29:06.50,FR,,0,0,0,,L'hégémonie mondiale, au bas mot.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.37,0:29:12.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Que fait une locomotive dans la Zone ?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.91,0:29:16.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Elle dessert les postes de garde\Net n'ira pas plus loin.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.25,0:29:19.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils n'aiment pas y aller.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.01,0:29:26.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Tout le monde en place !
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.18,0:29:28.64,FR,,0,0,0,,Tout le monde est là ?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.14,0:29:32.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Les veilleurs de nuit sont arrivés.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.06,0:29:35.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Éteignez la télévision !
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.38,0:30:43.55,FR,,0,0,0,,Plus vite !
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.69,0:31:40.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Écoutez bien.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.52,0:31:45.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Allez voir si la draisine\Nest sur la voie.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.28,0:31:47.74,FR,,0,0,0,,- Quelle draisine ?\N- Allez-y !
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.51,0:32:12.55,FR,,0,0,0,,Laissez, je vais le faire.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.17,0:34:10.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Le jerrycan !
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.45,0:34:42.24,FR,,0,0,0,,Laissez tomber votre sac,\Nil nous gêne.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.45,0:34:45.04,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est plutôt vous qui voyagez léger.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.92,0:34:51.09,FR,,0,0,0,,Si vous êtes touché,\Nne criez pas, ne bougez pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.25,0:34:53.17,FR,,0,0,0,,S'ils vous voient, ils vous tuent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.46,0:34:57.21,FR,,0,0,0,,Plus tard, quand tout est calme,\Nrampez vers le poste de garde.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.43,0:34:59.14,FR,,0,0,0,,On vous récupérera le matin.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.99,0:35:17.99,FR,,0,0,0,,- Ils ne nous rattraperont pas ?\N- Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.61,0:35:20.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils en ont peur comme de la peste.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.58,0:35:22.87,FR,,0,0,0,,Peur de qui ?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.00,0:39:44.04,FR,,0,0,0,,Voilà.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.71,0:39:47.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Nous sommes arrivés.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.80,0:39:52.09,FR,,0,0,0,,Quel silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.93,0:39:57.81,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est l'endroit le plus calme\Nde la Terre.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.31,0:40:01.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous le verrez vous-mêmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.27,0:40:04.90,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est si beau ici.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.19,0:40:06.69,FR,,0,0,0,,Il n'y a personne.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.07,0:40:08.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Nous sommes là, nous.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.78,0:40:11.87,FR,,0,0,0,,Trois hommes ne peuvent pas\Ntout souiller en un jour.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.07,0:40:14.53,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment ça ? Bien sûr que si.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.25,0:40:21.50,FR,,0,0,0,,Bizarre,\Nles fleurs n'ont pas d'odeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.13,0:40:25.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous ne sentez pas ?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.46,0:40:28.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça pue la vase, c'est ce que je sens.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.42,0:40:31.09,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça c'est la rivière,\Nelle est tout près.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.14,0:40:34.18,FR,,0,0,0,,Il y avait des fleurs pas loin.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.39,0:40:36.64,FR,,0,0,0,,Porc-épic les a écrasées un jour.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.85,0:40:38.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Rayées de la carte.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.81,0:40:41.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais l'odeur des fleurs est restée.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.56,0:40:44.06,FR,,0,0,0,,De longues années.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.07,0:40:47.86,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi les a-t-il écrasées ?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.65,0:40:49.94,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne sais pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.82,0:40:53.99,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi aussi je lui ai demandé.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.03,0:40:57.41,FR,,0,0,0,,Il a dit qu'un jour je comprendrai.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.20,0:41:03.50,FR,,0,0,0,,Je pense qu'il a simplement\Ncommencé à haïr la Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.67,0:41:10.80,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est son vrai nom, Porc-épic ?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.51,0:41:14.22,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est un surnom, comme le vôtre.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.89,0:41:19.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Il a amené des gens dans la Zone\Npendant des années, il y tenait.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.35,0:41:21.77,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est mon maître.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.10,0:41:24.85,FR,,0,0,0,,Il m'a ouvert les yeux.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.73,0:41:30.77,FR,,0,0,0,,À l'époque,\Non ne l'appelait pas Porc-épic,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.99,0:41:32.53,FR,,0,0,0,,on l'appelait Maître.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.45,0:41:36.99,FR,,0,0,0,,Et puis, il a changé.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.95,0:41:39.99,FR,,0,0,0,,Quelque chose s'est brisé en lui.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.46,0:41:43.71,FR,,0,0,0,,À mon avis il a simplement été puni.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.92,0:41:48.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Pouvez-vous attacher\Nces bandelettes aux écrous ?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.17,0:41:52.97,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi, je vais aller faire un tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.93,0:41:56.18,FR,,0,0,0,,Je dois...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.78,0:42:12.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne vous éloignez pas trop.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.70,0:42:20.12,FR,,0,0,0,,Où va-t-il ?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.66,0:42:23.83,FR,,0,0,0,,Peut-être veut-il rester seul.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.04,0:42:25.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi ?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.54,0:42:29.25,FR,,0,0,0,,Même tous les trois,\Non ne se sent pas très à l'aise ici.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.05,0:42:34.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Un rendez-vous avec la Zone.\NC'est un Stalker, lui.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.76,0:42:37.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Et alors ?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.51,0:42:42.64,FR,,0,0,0,,Être Stalker est une vocation,\Nen quelque sorte.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.31,0:42:45.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Je l'imaginais différent.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.69,0:42:46.94,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment ?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.15,0:42:51.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Le genre {\i1}Histoires de Bas-de-Cuir,{\i0}\N{\i1}Chingachgook, Grand Serpent...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.03,0:42:55.33,FR,,0,0,0,,Son histoire à lui\Nest plus terrible que ça.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.53,0:42:58.95,FR,,0,0,0,,Il a fait plusieurs fois de la prison,\Nil s'est blessé ici.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.16,0:43:02.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Sa fille est une mutante.\N"Victime de la Zone", comme on dit.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.83,0:43:04.79,FR,,0,0,0,,On dit qu'elle n'a pas de jambes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.79,0:43:11.59,FR,,0,0,0,,Qu'en est-il de ce Porc-épic ?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.46,0:43:15.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Que signifie "Il a été puni"?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.01,0:43:18.05,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est une figure de style ?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.76,0:43:25.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Un jour, Porc-épic est revenu d'ici,\Nde la Zone,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.81,0:43:29.40,FR,,0,0,0,,et subitement il est devenu riche.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.90,0:43:32.61,FR,,0,0,0,,Incroyablement riche.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.77,0:43:34.77,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est une punition, ça ?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.28,0:43:39.12,FR,,0,0,0,,Une semaine après, il s'est pendu.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.57,0:43:40.82,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi ?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.20,0:43:42.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Chut !
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.54,0:43:47.54,FR,,0,0,0,,Et ça, qu'est-ce que c'est ?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.28,0:45:45.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Il y a une vingtaine d'années,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.78,0:45:48.58,FR,,0,0,0,,une météorite serait tombée\Nà cet endroit.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.50,0:45:51.92,FR,,0,0,0,,Le village a été réduit en cendres.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.00,0:45:54.75,FR,,0,0,0,,On a cherché cette météorite.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.96,0:45:57.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Bien sûr,\Nelle n'a jamais été retrouvée.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.34,0:46:01.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi "bien sûr"?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.67,0:46:04.51,FR,,0,0,0,,Puis, les gens se sont mis\Nà disparaître.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.26,0:46:07.97,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils venaient ici\Net ne revenaient pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.18,0:46:09.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Et alors ?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.06,0:46:14.94,FR,,0,0,0,,Finalement, on a conclu\Nque cette météorite
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.94,0:46:17.98,FR,,0,0,0,,n'en était pas vraiment une.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.73,0:46:20.15,FR,,0,0,0,,Pour commencer,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.24,0:46:25.45,FR,,0,0,0,,ils ont posé des barbelés
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.99,0:46:28.83,FR,,0,0,0,,pour que les curieux\Nne s'y aventurent pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.37,0:46:34.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Des rumeurs se sont alors répandues
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.46,0:46:37.00,FR,,0,0,0,,qu'il y avait un endroit dans la Zone
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.46,0:46:41.84,FR,,0,0,0,,où tous les désirs étaient exaucés.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.34,0:46:43.88,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors évidemment,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.93,0:46:49.35,FR,,0,0,0,,ils ont protégé la Zone\Ncomme la prunelle de leurs yeux.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.81,0:46:54.61,FR,,0,0,0,,Car il faut se méfier des désirs\Nqui pourraient surgir.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.35,0:46:58.81,FR,,0,0,0,,Si ce n'était pas une météorite,\Nqu'était-ce alors ?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.82,0:47:03.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Je le répète, on l'ignore.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.15,0:47:07.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais vous, qu'en pensez-vous ?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.41,0:47:10.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Je n'en pense rien.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.74,0:47:12.99,FR,,0,0,0,,Peu m'importe.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.29,0:47:19.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce serait un message à l'humanité,\Ncomme dit l'un de mes collègues.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.63,0:47:21.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Ou un cadeau.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.30,0:47:28.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Un drôle de cadeau.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.47,0:47:33.77,FR,,0,0,0,,- Pourquoi l'auraient-ils fait ?\N- Pour nous rendre heureux.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.06,0:47:42.32,FR,,0,0,0,,Les fleurs éclosent de nouveau,\Nmais elles ne sentent plus.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.28,0:47:46.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Excusez-moi de vous avoir laissés ici,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.78,0:47:49.45,FR,,0,0,0,,mais il était encore trop tôt\Npour y aller.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.87,0:47:54.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous avez entendu ?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.33,0:47:58.04,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce serait donc vrai\Nque des gens habitent ici ?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.08,0:48:00.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Qui ça ?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.21,0:48:04.80,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous me l'avez raconté vous-même.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.01,0:48:09.81,FR,,0,0,0,,Ces touristes qui se trouvaient ici,\Nquand la Zone s'est créée.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.39,0:48:13.23,FR,,0,0,0,,Il ne peut y avoir personne\Ndans la Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.98,0:48:19.77,FR,,0,0,0,,Bon, il faut y aller.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.82,0:49:08.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment reviendrons-nous ?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.32,0:49:11.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Ici, on ne revient pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.49,0:49:12.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment ça ?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.03,0:49:16.41,FR,,0,0,0,,Nous avancerons comme convenu.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.21,0:49:24.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Chaque fois,\Nj'indiquerai la direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.17,0:49:27.51,FR,,0,0,0,,Il est dangereux de s'en écarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.76,0:49:32.93,FR,,0,0,0,,Le premier point de repère\Nest ce dernier poteau.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.39,0:49:34.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Allez-y.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.05,0:49:37.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Passez le premier, Professeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.98,0:49:50.32,FR,,0,0,0,,À vous, maintenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.83,0:50:00.79,FR,,0,0,0,,Marchez bien dans ses traces.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.03,0:51:23.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Mon Dieu, mais où sont...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.62,0:51:27.83,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors ils seraient restés ici,\Nces gens ?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.21,0:51:29.63,FR,,0,0,0,,Qui sait ?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.92,0:51:33.97,FR,,0,0,0,,Je me souviens juste qu'ils montaient\Ndans des trains
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.17,0:51:36.51,FR,,0,0,0,,pour venir ici, dans la Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.09,0:51:38.88,FR,,0,0,0,,J'étais encore gosse.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.51,0:51:42.64,FR,,0,0,0,,Les gens croyaient qu'une invasion\Nse préparait.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.85,0:51:44.02,FR,,0,0,0,,Quelle bêtise.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.61,0:51:52.32,FR,,0,0,0,,Allez-y, Professeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.91,0:52:02.45,FR,,0,0,0,,À vous, l'Écrivain.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.77,0:54:34.77,FR,,0,0,0,,La Chambre est là-bas.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.65,0:54:38.36,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est là que nous allons.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.82,0:54:43.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous avez un peu exagéré,\Nc'est à deux pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.03,0:54:48.20,FR,,0,0,0,,Oui, mais il faudrait faire\Nde très grands pas.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.79,0:54:51.58,FR,,0,0,0,,On n'en fait pas de si grands.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.98,0:56:00.65,FR,,0,0,0,,Arrêtez, c'est interdit !
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.44,0:56:03.44,FR,,0,0,0,,Non.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.65,0:56:04.99,FR,,0,0,0,,N'y touchez pas !
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.70,0:56:09.49,FR,,0,0,0,,N'y touchez pas, je vous dis !
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.03,0:56:11.20,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça va pas ?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.78,0:56:12.99,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous êtes fou ?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.37,0:56:14.79,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça va pas ?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.66,0:56:19.33,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce n'est pas un lieu de promenade.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.54,0:56:23.46,FR,,0,0,0,,La Zone demande du respect,\Nsinon elle châtie.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.67,0:56:24.76,FR,,0,0,0,,Elle châtie ?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.96,0:56:27.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Essayez donc encore une fois.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.38,0:56:29.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous avez perdu votre langue ?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.89,0:56:32.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Je vous l'avais demandé.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.80,0:56:34.09,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est par là ?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.39,0:56:39.23,FR,,0,0,0,,Oui, on monte, on entre,\Npuis à gauche.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.40,0:56:41.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais ne passons pas par là.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.36,0:56:44.86,FR,,0,0,0,,Nous ferons le tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.82,0:56:47.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Et pourquoi ça ?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.70,0:56:52.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Dans la Zone, le chemin le plus droit\Nn'est pas le plus court.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.57,0:56:54.95,FR,,0,0,0,,Plus on va loin, moins on risque.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.41,0:56:58.95,FR,,0,0,0,,- Tout droit, il y a danger de mort ?\N- C'est dangereux, vous dit-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.16,0:57:03.04,FR,,0,0,0,,- Et en faisant le tour ?\N- Ça l'est aussi. On ne passe pas ici.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.25,0:57:06.63,FR,,0,0,0,,Peu importe où on ne doit pas passer.\NEt si je veux...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.84,0:57:08.09,FR,,0,0,0,,Écoutez.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.42,0:57:12.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi faire un détour,\Nsi c'est juste là ?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.34,0:57:14.38,FR,,0,0,0,,Il y a un risque de toute façon.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.56,0:57:15.73,FR,,0,0,0,,On s'en fiche.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.93,0:57:19.31,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous le prenez trop à la légère.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.19,0:57:24.44,FR,,0,0,0,,J'en ai marre de vos écrous\Net de vos bandelettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.65,0:57:28.36,FR,,0,0,0,,Faites ce que vous voulez,\Nmoi je passe par ici.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.57,0:57:31.53,FR,,0,0,0,,- Il a perdu la raison.\N- Vous pouvez parler...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.16,0:57:33.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous permettez ?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.67,0:57:47.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Le vent se lève.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.21,0:57:50.50,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous sentez ?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.01,0:57:52.18,FR,,0,0,0,,L'herbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.73,0:58:03.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors, raison de plus.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.69,0:58:06.36,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment ça ?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.08,0:58:25.63,FR,,0,0,0,,- Attendez.\N- Lâchez-moi.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.71,0:58:27.84,FR,,0,0,0,,Bien.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.09,0:58:32.18,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais alors,\Nje prends le professeur à témoin.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.38,0:58:35.84,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne vous ai pas envoyé,\Nvous y allez de votre plein gré.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.05,0:58:38.26,FR,,0,0,0,,Parfaitement. Quoi encore ?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.14,0:58:41.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Rien, allez-y.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.48,0:58:50.94,FR,,0,0,0,,J'espère que vous aurez de la chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.75,0:59:07.04,FR,,0,0,0,,Écoutez.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.71,0:59:10.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Si soudain vous remarquez\Nquelque chose
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.63,0:59:13.84,FR,,0,0,0,,ou si vous ressentez\Nquelque chose d'insolite,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.01,0:59:16.76,FR,,0,0,0,,revenez immédiatement, sinon...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.97,0:59:20.18,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne me jetez pas votre ferraille\Ndans la nuque.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.08,1:00:30.75,FR,,0,0,0,,Halte, ne bougez pas.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.71,1:00:36.92,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi ?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.26,1:00:38.89,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment ?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.18,1:00:41.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi l'avez-vous arrêté ?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.43,1:00:44.64,FR,,0,0,0,,Je pensais que c'était vous.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.22,1:01:25.72,FR,,0,0,0,,Que s'est-il passé ?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.68,1:01:28.97,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi m'avoir dit de m'arrêter ?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.18,1:01:32.98,FR,,0,0,0,,- Ce n'était pas moi.\N- Qui alors ? Vous ?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.40,1:01:39.19,FR,,0,0,0,,Que diable...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.70,1:01:44.41,FR,,0,0,0,,Chapeau, camarade Shakespeare !
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.62,1:01:47.54,FR,,0,0,0,,Avancer vous faisait peur,\Nreculer vous faisait honte,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.74,1:01:51.29,FR,,0,0,0,,alors vous vous êtes donné cet ordre\Nd'une voix déguisée.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.50,1:01:53.92,FR,,0,0,0,,La peur vous a même fait dessaouler.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.13,1:01:55.67,FR,,0,0,0,,- Quoi ?\N- Ça suffit.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.13,1:02:00.09,FR,,0,0,0,,- Et ma bouteille ?\N- Ça suffit, je vous dis !
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.65,1:02:19.95,FR,,0,0,0,,La Zone est un système très complexe
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.86,1:02:24.24,FR,,0,0,0,,de pièges.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.07,1:02:26.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils sont tous mortels.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.50,1:02:32.84,FR,,0,0,0,,J'ignore ce qui se passe\Nen l'absence des hommes,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.04,1:02:35.42,FR,,0,0,0,,mais dès qu'ils apparaissent,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.83,1:02:38.42,FR,,0,0,0,,tout se met en mouvement.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.05,1:02:44.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Des pièges disparaissent,\Nd'autres les remplacent.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.55,1:02:48.89,FR,,0,0,0,,Les endroits qui étaient sûrs\Ndeviennent infranchissables.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.81,1:02:52.65,FR,,0,0,0,,Le chemin est tantôt\Nsimple et facile,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.81,1:02:54.94,FR,,0,0,0,,tantôt semé d'embûches.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.53,1:03:01.07,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est ça, la Zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.61,1:03:05.82,FR,,0,0,0,,On pourrait la croire capricieuse,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.37,1:03:09.46,FR,,0,0,0,,mais elle est juste à chaque instant
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.66,1:03:12.12,FR,,0,0,0,,le produit de notre propre\Nétat d'esprit.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.42,1:03:16.76,FR,,0,0,0,,J'avoue qu'il est arrivé que des gens
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.92,1:03:20.47,FR,,0,0,0,,abandonnent à mi-chemin\Net repartent bredouilles.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.42,1:03:24.92,FR,,0,0,0,,D'autres sont morts au seuil même\Nde la Chambre.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.01,1:03:29.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Tout ce qui se passe ici ne dépend pas\Nde la Zone, mais de nous.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.76,1:03:33.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Elle laisse passer les bons\Net anéantit les méchants ?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.06,1:03:36.31,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne sais pas.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.52,1:03:41.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Je crois qu'elle laisse passer\Nceux qui n'ont plus aucun espoir.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.44,1:03:44.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce ne sont pas les bons\Nou les mauvais.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.36,1:03:46.95,FR,,0,0,0,,Les malheureux, plutôt.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.82,1:03:50.32,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais même le plus malheureux\Npérira vite
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.53,1:03:52.41,FR,,0,0,0,,s'il ne sait pas se conduire.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.00,1:04:05.67,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous avez de la chance\Nqu'elle vous ait prévenu.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.05,1:04:13.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous savez,\Nje préfère vous attendre ici
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.97,1:04:16.31,FR,,0,0,0,,jusqu'à ce que vous reveniez
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.27,1:04:19.15,FR,,0,0,0,,comblés de félicité.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.73,1:04:21.40,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.65,1:04:24.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais si, j'ai des sandwichs,\Nun thermos.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.90,1:04:26.99,FR,,0,0,0,,Sans moi,\Nvous ne tiendrez pas une heure.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.20,1:04:28.20,FR,,0,0,0,,Et ensuite ?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.41,1:04:31.33,FR,,0,0,0,,On ne revient pas par le chemin\Nde l'aller.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.37,1:04:35.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Je préférerais quand même...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.58,1:04:38.00,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors repartons tous ensemble.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.58,1:04:40.50,FR,,0,0,0,,Je vous rendrai votre argent.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.71,1:04:44.80,FR,,0,0,0,,J'en déduirai une partie\Npour le dérangement.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.88,1:04:48.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous voilà dégrisé, Professeur ?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.22,1:04:56.14,FR,,0,0,0,,Très bien, jetez votre écrou.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.07,1:05:52.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Deuxième partie
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.95,1:06:00.75,FR,,0,0,0,,STALKER
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.54,1:06:06.54,FR,,0,0,0,,Où êtes-vous ? Venez par ici.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.93,1:06:13.72,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous êtes fatigués ?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.32,1:06:30.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Mon Dieu !
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.53,1:06:39.20,FR,,0,0,0,,À en juger par son ton,\Nil va encore nous dire quoi faire.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.76,1:07:01.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Que ce qui est planifié\Ns'accomplisse.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.77,1:07:04.61,FR,,0,0,0,,Puissent-ils croire
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.73,1:07:09.61,FR,,0,0,0,,et rire de leurs propres passions.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.32,1:07:14.82,FR,,0,0,0,,Car ce qu'ils nomment passions\Nn'est pas la force de l'âme,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.03,1:07:18.58,FR,,0,0,0,,mais une friction entre l'âme\Net le monde extérieur.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.62,1:07:22.92,FR,,0,0,0,,L'essentiel est qu'ils croient\Nen eux-mêmes
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.79,1:07:26.92,FR,,0,0,0,,et deviennent fragiles\Ncomme des enfants.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.54,1:07:31.67,FR,,0,0,0,,Car la faiblesse est grande\Ntandis que la force est minime.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.34,1:07:39.64,FR,,0,0,0,,L'homme, en venant au monde,\Nest faible et souple.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.31,1:07:43.10,FR,,0,0,0,,Quand il meurt, il est fort et dur.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.69,1:07:47.86,FR,,0,0,0,,L'arbre qui pousse\Nest tendre et souple.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.15,1:07:52.15,FR,,0,0,0,,Devenu sec et dur, il meurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.74,1:07:57.95,FR,,0,0,0,,La dureté et la force\Nsont les compagnons de la mort.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.41,1:08:03.46,FR,,0,0,0,,La souplesse et la faiblesse\Nexpriment la fraîcheur de la vie.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.87,1:08:09.00,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est pourquoi ce qui est durci\Nne vaincra jamais.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.31,1:08:30.69,FR,,0,0,0,,Venez par ici !
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.90,1:08:34.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Nous avons bien marché.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.99,1:08:37.41,FR,,0,0,0,,Au tunnel sec, ce sera plus facile.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.57,1:08:39.41,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous avez parlé trop vite.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.62,1:08:41.54,FR,,0,0,0,,Nous avançons déjà ?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.87,1:08:44.21,FR,,0,0,0,,Bien sûr. Pourquoi ?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.41,1:08:49.67,FR,,0,0,0,,Je pensais que vous vouliez juste\Nnous montrer quelque chose ici.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.88,1:08:53.17,FR,,0,0,0,,- Et mon sac à dos ?\N- Qu'est-il arrivé à votre sac ?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.38,1:08:57.38,FR,,0,0,0,,Je l'ai laissé là-bas.\NJe ne savais pas qu'on avançait.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.97,1:09:02.35,FR,,0,0,0,,- On n'y peut plus rien.\N- Si, il faut qu'on y retourne.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.55,1:09:04.89,FR,,0,0,0,,- Impossible.\N- Il me faut mon sac !
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.06,1:09:09.57,FR,,0,0,0,,On ne revient ni en arrière\Nni par le même chemin.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.48,1:09:15.11,FR,,0,0,0,,Au diable ce sac.\NQu'avez-vous dedans, des diamants ?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.32,1:09:18.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous oubliez que la Chambre\Nvous donnera tout ce que vous voulez.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.07,1:09:22.82,FR,,0,0,0,,Des sacs à dos en pagaille\Nsi vous voulez.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.03,1:09:25.28,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est encore loin, cette Chambre ?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.74,1:09:29.04,FR,,0,0,0,,En ligne droite,\Nce serait à 200 mètres.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.25,1:09:31.84,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais il n'y a pas\Nde lignes droites ici.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.34,1:09:36.59,FR,,0,0,0,,Oubliez votre empirisme incessant,\NProfesseur.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.38,1:09:40.01,FR,,0,0,0,,Les miracles sont en dehors\Nde l'empirisme.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.39,1:09:44.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Rappelez-vous que saint Pierre\Na failli se noyer.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.98,1:09:50.61,FR,,0,0,0,,Allez-y, l'Écrivain.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.60,1:09:53.89,FR,,0,0,0,,Où ça ?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.77,1:09:56.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Montez cet escalier.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.87,1:10:09.21,FR,,0,0,0,,Professeur, où êtes-vous passé ?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.48,1:12:02.27,FR,,0,0,0,,Et voilà le tunnel sec.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.65,1:12:04.49,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous appelez ça sec ?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.32,1:12:08.03,FR,,0,0,0,,Plaisanterie locale.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.82,1:12:11.41,FR,,0,0,0,,D'habitude,\Nil faut passer à la nage.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.27,1:12:42.31,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais où est le Professeur ?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.52,1:12:43.52,FR,,0,0,0,,Quoi ?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.28,1:12:45.82,FR,,0,0,0,,Le Professeur a disparu.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.03,1:12:47.49,FR,,0,0,0,,Professeur ! Professeur !
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.95,1:12:50.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Il marchait derrière vous, pourtant.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.33,1:12:54.58,FR,,0,0,0,,Il a dû s'arrêter quelque part\Net il s'est perdu.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.79,1:12:58.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Non, il a dû aller chercher son sac.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.04,1:13:01.25,FR,,0,0,0,,Il ne pourra pas s'en sortir.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.25,1:13:03.50,FR,,0,0,0,,On l'attend ici ?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.71,1:13:07.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Non, pas ici.\NTout change à chaque instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.30,1:13:08.84,FR,,0,0,0,,On continue à deux.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.54,1:13:41.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Regardez, qu'est-ce que c'est ?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.50,1:13:44.96,FR,,0,0,0,,- Je vous l'ai pourtant expliqué.\N- Expliqué ?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.13,1:13:47.22,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est la Zone, vous comprenez.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.63,1:13:50.55,FR,,0,0,0,,Vite, venez vite.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.66,1:14:12.99,FR,,0,0,0,,Le voilà.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.59,1:14:30.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Je vous suis très reconnaissant\Nd'avoir...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.55,1:14:32.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment êtes-vous arrivé ici ?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.60,1:14:37.02,FR,,0,0,0,,Une grande partie du chemin,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.68,1:14:40.72,FR,,0,0,0,,j'ai rampé à quatre pattes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.81,1:14:44.81,FR,,0,0,0,,Incroyable.\NComment nous avez-vous devancés ?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.06,1:14:48.23,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment ça, devancés ?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.32,1:14:52.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Je suis revenu chercher mon sac à dos.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.91,1:14:56.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Notre écrou, que fait-il ici ?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.04,1:15:00.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Seigneur.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.21,1:15:03.71,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est un piège.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.71,1:15:11.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Porc-épic a accroché\Nun écrou ici exprès.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.18,1:15:19.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment la Zone nous a-t-elle\Nlaissés passer ?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.32,1:15:30.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne ferai plus un pas tant que...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.94,1:15:33.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça alors.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.95,1:15:40.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça suffit.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.75,1:15:43.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Repos.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.63,1:15:59.93,FR,,0,0,0,,Tenez-vous loin de l'écrou,\Non ne sait jamais.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.18,1:16:05.39,FR,,0,0,0,,J'ai bien cru que le Professeur\Nne s'en sortirait pas.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.77,1:16:13.11,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne sais jamais à l'avance\Nquelles personnes je conduis.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.28,1:16:15.20,FR,,0,0,0,,Tout se précise ici,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.86,1:16:17.86,FR,,0,0,0,,quand il est trop tard.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.70,1:16:21.54,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne vous en faites pas pour nous,\Ntout va bien.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.74,1:16:24.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Sac et caleçons sont sains et saufs.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.12,1:16:30.25,FR,,0,0,0,,N'y fourrez pas votre nez,\Nsi vous ne comprenez pas.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.46,1:16:33.09,FR,,0,0,0,,Qu'y a-t-il à comprendre exactement ?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.67,1:16:35.46,FR,,0,0,0,,Les lois de Newton...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.18,1:16:39.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Quelle affaire !\NÉtudier les abîmes psychologiques.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.18,1:16:42.77,FR,,0,0,0,,À l'Institut, on est mal vu.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.93,1:16:46.31,FR,,0,0,0,,On ne donne pas de fonds\Npour les expéditions,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.52,1:16:50.94,FR,,0,0,0,,alors on bourre son sac de manomètres\Net merdomètres,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.61,1:16:55.36,FR,,0,0,0,,pour pénétrer illégalement\Ndans la Zone,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.49,1:16:58.99,FR,,0,0,0,,croire à ses miracles\Ngrâce à l'algèbre.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.70,1:17:05.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Personne au monde ne connaît\Nl'existence de la Zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.29,1:17:07.54,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors, ça fait sensation.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.62,1:17:12.04,FR,,0,0,0,,La télévision, les admiratrices\Nqui bavent devant vous,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.25,1:17:14.21,FR,,0,0,0,,les couronnes de laurier...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.05,1:17:19.89,FR,,0,0,0,,Apparaît le professeur,\Ntout de blanc vêtu,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.30,1:17:21.76,FR,,0,0,0,,qui annonce :
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.05,1:17:24.51,FR,,0,0,0,,"Mane, Thecel, Phares".
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.81,1:17:27.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Les gens sont sidérés
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.52,1:17:33.19,FR,,0,0,0,,et hurlent en chœur :\N"Donnez-lui le prix Nobel".
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.61,1:17:38.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Minable scribouillard.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.95,1:17:41.33,FR,,0,0,0,,Psychologue à la noix.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.20,1:17:45.62,FR,,0,0,0,,Écrivez donc\Nsur les murs des chiottes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.24,1:17:48.03,FR,,0,0,0,,Baratineur de bas étage.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.00,1:17:53.05,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est mou, tout ça.\NVous n'êtes pas à la hauteur.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.67,1:17:57.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous ne savez pas y faire.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.80,1:18:01.05,FR,,0,0,0,,D'accord.\NDisons que je vise un prix Nobel.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.64,1:18:04.10,FR,,0,0,0,,Et vous, vous courez après quoi ?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.72,1:18:09.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous voulez offrir à l'humanité\Nles perles de votre vénale inspiration ?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.14,1:18:13.23,FR,,0,0,0,,Je me fous de l'humanité.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.11,1:18:18.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Une seule personne m'intéresse\Ndans toute cette humanité : moi.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.11,1:18:22.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Je tiens à savoir\Nsi je vaux quelque chose
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.78,1:18:25.91,FR,,0,0,0,,ou si je suis une merde,\Ncomme certains le sont.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.91,1:18:30.46,FR,,0,0,0,,Et si vous découvrez\Nque vous êtes en fait...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.66,1:18:32.95,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous savez, Monsieur Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.63,1:18:36.30,FR,,0,0,0,,je ne souhaite pas discuter avec vous.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.80,1:18:43.10,FR,,0,0,0,,De la discussion jaillit la vérité.\NQu'elle soit maudite.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.05,1:18:48.93,FR,,0,0,0,,Écoutez, Chingachgook.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.35,1:18:56.27,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous avez conduit des tas de gens ici.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.48,1:19:00.82,FR,,0,0,0,,Pas autant que j'aurais voulu.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.74,1:19:03.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Là n'est pas la question.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.95,1:19:07.25,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi venaient-ils ici ?\NQue voulaient-ils ?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.45,1:19:12.96,FR,,0,0,0,,- Trouver leur bonheur, je pense.\N- Quel genre de bonheur ?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.92,1:19:19.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Les gens ne parlent pas\Nde ce qui leur est le plus cher.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.42,1:19:23.26,FR,,0,0,0,,Et ça ne nous regarde pas,\Nni vous ni moi.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.34,1:19:27.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous avez bien de la chance\Nen tout cas.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.26,1:19:31.22,FR,,0,0,0,,De ma vie je n'ai jamais rencontré\Nun seul homme heureux.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.60,1:19:32.93,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi non plus.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.02,1:19:37.32,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils sortent de la Chambre,\Nje les reconduis
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.52,1:19:40.11,FR,,0,0,0,,et on ne se revoit plus jamais.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.19,1:19:45.32,FR,,0,0,0,,Les désirs ne se réalisent pas\Nimmédiatement.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.16,1:19:48.33,FR,,0,0,0,,Et vous, cette Chambrette
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.53,1:19:52.07,FR,,0,0,0,,ne vous a jamais tenté\Npersonnellement ?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.17,1:19:59.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Je suis bien comme je suis.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.68,1:20:54.14,FR,,0,0,0,,Professeur, écoutez-moi.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.27,1:20:59.44,FR,,0,0,0,,À propos de l'inspiration vénale.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.07,1:21:04.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Admettons que j'entre\Ndans cette Chambre,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.07,1:21:09.28,FR,,0,0,0,,et que je revienne\Ndans notre petite ville en vrai génie.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.50,1:21:20.92,FR,,0,0,0,,L'homme écrit parce qu'il souffre,\Nil doute.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.21,1:21:27.09,FR,,0,0,0,,Il doit sans cesse prouver aux autres\Net à lui-même
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.30,1:21:29.43,FR,,0,0,0,,qu'il vaut quelque chose.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.85,1:21:35.31,FR,,0,0,0,,Or, si je sais avec certitude\Nque je suis un génie,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.39,1:21:39.52,FR,,0,0,0,,alors pourquoi écrire ?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.94,1:21:43.65,FR,,0,0,0,,À quoi bon ?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.86,1:21:52.57,FR,,0,0,0,,D'ailleurs je dois vous dire\Nque nous existons uniquement pour...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.74,1:21:56.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Soyez gentil, laissez-moi tranquille.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.00,1:22:02.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Laissez-moi somnoler au moins,\Nje n'ai pas dormi de la nuit.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.34,1:22:05.80,FR,,0,0,0,,Gardez vos complexes pour vous.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.71,1:22:08.80,FR,,0,0,0,,De toute façon,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.13,1:22:11.92,FR,,0,0,0,,toute votre technologie,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.26,1:22:17.85,FR,,0,0,0,,ces hauts fourneaux, ces roues,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.85,1:22:23.77,FR,,0,0,0,,et tout ce remue-ménage,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.98,1:22:27.82,FR,,0,0,0,,en vue de travailler moins\Net bouffer davantage,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.45,1:22:32.37,FR,,0,0,0,,ne sont que béquilles et prothèses.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.16,1:22:38.79,FR,,0,0,0,,L'humanité existe pour créer.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.29,1:22:43.58,FR,,0,0,0,,Créer des œuvres d'art.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.50,1:22:47.54,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça ne lui apporte rien,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.75,1:22:50.88,FR,,0,0,0,,contrairement\Naux autres actions humaines.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.09,1:22:55.47,FR,,0,0,0,,Quelles grandes illusions.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.68,1:22:58.52,FR,,0,0,0,,Images d'une vérité absolue.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.31,1:23:02.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous m'écoutez, Professeur ?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.40,1:23:06.15,FR,,0,0,0,,De quel altruisme parlez-vous
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.36,1:23:09.65,FR,,0,0,0,,alors que des gens\Nmeurent encore de faim ?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.86,1:23:11.95,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous débarquez d'où, de la lune ?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.41,1:23:25.04,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est ça, notre aristocratie\Nintellectuelle ?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.71,1:23:29.84,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous ne savez pas raisonner\Nde façon abstraite.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.47,1:23:33.76,FR,,0,0,0,,Est-ce que vous essayez
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.72,1:23:37.64,FR,,0,0,0,,de m'apprendre le sens de la vie ?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.52,1:23:42.77,FR,,0,0,0,,Et à raisonner, dans la foulée ?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.56,1:23:45.15,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est inutile.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.31,1:23:50.27,FR,,0,0,0,,Bien que professeur,\Nvous êtes ignare.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.83,1:24:44.13,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Il y eut alors un violent\Ntremblement de terre{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.54,1:24:49.09,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Le soleil devint sombre\Ntel un cilice{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.96,1:24:52.17,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Et la lune devint\Nrouge comme le sang{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.21,1:24:57.96,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Les étoiles du ciel\Ntombèrent sur la Terre{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.18,1:25:02.02,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}comme un figuier secoué\Npar un vent violent{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.47,1:25:06.22,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}dont les figues, encore vertes,\Ntombent à terre.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.98,1:25:10.69,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Et le ciel disparut,\Ncomme un parchemin qu'on roule.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.32,1:25:15.57,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Les montagnes\Net les îles s'arrachèrent{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.78,1:25:17.78,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}de leurs places...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.87,1:25:26.54,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Les rois de la Terre\Net les grands de ce monde{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.46,1:25:31.21,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}et les riches et les chiliarques,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.67,1:25:36.88,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}les hommes forts et les hommes libres{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.80,1:25:41.68,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}se cachèrent dans les cavernes\Net dans les gorges{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.89,1:25:45.98,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}disant aux montagnes\Net aux pierres : "Tombez sur nous{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.18,1:25:50.31,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"et cachez-nous\Nde celui qui siège sur le trône,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.77,1:25:53.61,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"épargnez-nous la colère de l'Agneau.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.77,1:25:57.23,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Car est arrivé\Nle grand jour de Sa colère.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.15,1:26:01.82,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Qui donc pourra survivre ?"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.46,1:29:05.04,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce jour-là,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.18,1:29:08.93,FR,,0,0,0,,deux d'entre eux
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.64,1:29:14.98,FR,,0,0,0,,allaient à un village éloigné\Nde soixante stades
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.81,1:29:17.65,FR,,0,0,0,,appelé...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.48,1:29:22.28,FR,,0,0,0,,et s'entretenaient\Nde tout ce qui s'était passé.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.48,1:29:25.61,FR,,0,0,0,,Et pendant qu'ils parlaient,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.82,1:29:29.95,FR,,0,0,0,,lui s'approcha et fit route avec eux.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.49,1:29:34.87,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais leurs yeux étaient retenus,\Nsi bien qu'ils ne le reconnurent pas.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.04,1:29:38.46,FR,,0,0,0,,Il leur dit : "De quoi parlez-vous
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.83,1:29:44.38,FR,,0,0,0,,et pourquoi êtes-vous tristes ?"
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.26,1:29:47.22,FR,,0,0,0,,l'un deux, appelé...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.44,1:30:02.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous voilà réveillés ?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.07,1:30:11.03,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous parliez du sens
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.74,1:30:14.95,FR,,0,0,0,,de notre vie.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.29,1:30:18.17,FR,,0,0,0,,De l'art désintéressé.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.25,1:30:24.25,FR,,0,0,0,,La musique, par exemple.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.34,1:30:33.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Elle est la moins liée à la réalité.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.14,1:30:38.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Quand elle l'est,\Nc'est sans idéologie, mécaniquement.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.27,1:30:41.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Par un son vide, sans associations.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.11,1:30:50.32,FR,,0,0,0,,Et pourtant, la musique,\Ncomme par miracle,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.86,1:30:53.24,FR,,0,0,0,,pénètre jusqu'au fond de l'âme.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.37,1:31:00.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Que fait résonner en nous\Nce bruit devenu harmonie ?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.25,1:31:04.92,FR,,0,0,0,,Et le transforme en source\Nd'extrême volupté
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.63,1:31:08.47,FR,,0,0,0,,qui nous unit et nous bouleverse ?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.01,1:31:14.14,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi tout cela et surtout,\Npour qui ?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.64,1:31:21.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous répondrez que c'est\Npour personne et pour rien,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.56,1:31:23.10,FR,,0,0,0,,que c'est désintéressé.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.73,1:31:26.15,FR,,0,0,0,,Eh bien, non.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.69,1:31:29.19,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est peu probable.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.36,1:31:34.36,FR,,0,0,0,,Car tout a un sens, finalement.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.45,1:31:39.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Un sens et une raison d'être.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.48,1:32:12.82,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est par là qu'il faut aller ?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.53,1:32:19.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Hélas, il n'y a pas d'autre voie.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.01,1:32:39.35,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est plutôt sombre,\Nn'est-ce pas, Professeur ?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.52,1:32:46.44,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne tiens pas à m'y aventurer\Nle premier.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.40,1:32:50.15,FR,,0,0,0,,Grand-Serpent\Nne se porte pas volontaire.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.94,1:32:56.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Pardon, nous devrons tirer au sort.\NVous n'êtes pas contre ?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.32,1:33:00.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Si, je préférerais un volontaire.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.24,1:33:05.03,FR,,0,0,0,,Avez-vous des allumettes ?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.21,1:33:14.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Merci.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.94,1:33:28.98,FR,,0,0,0,,La plus longue ira en premier.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.86,1:33:33.19,FR,,0,0,0,,Tirez.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.41,1:33:41.41,FR,,0,0,0,,La longue.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.16,1:33:44.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Cette fois-ci,\Nvous n'avez pas eu de chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.18,1:34:01.81,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous devriez y jeter un écrou,\Nau moins.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.35,1:34:04.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Bien sûr, voilà.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.05,1:34:43.26,FR,,0,0,0,,Encore un ?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.56,1:34:53.73,FR,,0,0,0,,Bon.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.61,1:34:56.78,FR,,0,0,0,,J'y vais.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.59,1:36:45.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Plus vite, Professeur.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:55.80,1:40:57.01,FR,,0,0,0,,Là !
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.60,1:41:02.77,FR,,0,0,0,,Il y a une porte.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.28,1:41:21.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Allez-y.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.91,1:41:25.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Ouvrez cette porte et entrez.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.46,1:41:34.63,FR,,0,0,0,,Encore moi ?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:35.38,1:41:37.13,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est moi qui entre ?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:37.30,1:41:39.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Le tirage au sort vous a désigné.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.10,1:41:43.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Allez, ne vous attardez pas ici.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.64,1:41:49.27,FR,,0,0,0,,Qu'est-ce que c'est ?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.77,1:41:51.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Surtout pas d'armes ici !
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.73,1:41:55.19,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est la mort pour vous\Ncomme pour nous.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.40,1:41:57.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Rappelez-vous les chars.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.15,1:41:59.94,FR,,0,0,0,,Jetez-le, je vous en prie !
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.16,1:42:02.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous ne comprenez pas ou quoi ?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.66,1:42:07.66,FR,,0,0,0,,S'il vous arrive quelque chose,\Nje vous tirerai de là.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.46,1:42:10.79,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais si...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.13,1:42:12.51,FR,,0,0,0,,Je vous en supplie.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.92,1:42:16.72,FR,,0,0,0,,Sur qui voulez-vous tirer, là-bas ?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.48,1:42:31.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Allez, nous avons peu de temps.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.98,1:42:37.61,FR,,0,0,0,,Il y a de l'eau ici.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.70,1:42:41.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Tenez-vous à la rampe et descendez.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.74,1:43:31.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Ensuite, attendez-nous là-haut,\Nà la sortie.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.39,1:43:49.23,FR,,0,0,0,,J'espère que vous n'avez rien\Ndans le genre ?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.39,1:43:50.52,FR,,0,0,0,,Quoi donc ?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.68,1:43:52.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Pas de pistolet ?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.73,1:43:55.44,FR,,0,0,0,,Non, j'ai une ampoule au cas où.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.40,1:43:57.99,FR,,0,0,0,,Quelle ampoule ?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.19,1:44:00.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Une ampoule cachée sur moi.\NDu poison.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.11,1:44:04.28,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est pour mourir\Nque vous êtes venu ici ?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.54,1:44:13.38,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est au cas où. On ne sait jamais.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.65,1:44:42.61,FR,,0,0,0,,L'Écrivain, en arrière !
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.82,1:44:45.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Revenez donc, c'est suicidaire !
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.45,1:44:47.79,FR,,0,0,0,,J'ai dit d'attendre à l'entrée.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.53,1:44:50.11,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne bougez pas !
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.58,1:45:39.00,FR,,0,0,0,,- Tout ça, c'est votre tunnel.\N- Quoi ?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.17,1:45:40.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Rien.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.79,1:45:43.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous auriez dû passer en premier.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.63,1:45:46.80,FR,,0,0,0,,Par peur, il s'est trompé de route.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.99,1:47:36.16,FR,,0,0,0,,Encore une expérience.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.66,1:47:41.16,FR,,0,0,0,,Les expériences, les faits...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.67,1:47:44.09,FR,,0,0,0,,La vérité enfin.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.84,1:47:49.47,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais les faits n'existent pas,\Nsurtout ici.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.76,1:47:53.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Ici, tout a été inventé par quelqu'un.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.80,1:47:57.55,FR,,0,0,0,,L'invention d'un imbécile,\Nvous ne le sentez pas ?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.18,1:48:03.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous voulez savoir à tout prix\Nqui a inventé ça.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.69,1:48:07.36,FR,,0,0,0,,Pour quoi faire ?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.57,1:48:11.07,FR,,0,0,0,,À quoi bon vos connaissances ?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.28,1:48:14.24,FR,,0,0,0,,Quelle conscience en souffrira ?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.45,1:48:15.78,FR,,0,0,0,,La mienne ?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.45,1:48:20.50,FR,,0,0,0,,Je n'ai pas de conscience,\Nje n'ai que des nerfs.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.83,1:48:23.75,FR,,0,0,0,,Un salaud m'engueule, ça me blesse.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.67,1:48:27.84,FR,,0,0,0,,Un autre salaud me flatte,\Nça me blesse encore.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.17,1:48:30.63,FR,,0,0,0,,On y met son âme et son cœur,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.84,1:48:33.68,FR,,0,0,0,,ils vous dévorent et l'âme et le cœur.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.43,1:48:38.89,FR,,0,0,0,,On sort une saleté de son âme\Net ils la bouffent.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.60,1:48:42.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils sont tous instruits,\Nsans exception.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.02,1:48:47.36,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils ont tous besoin\Nde stimulation sensorielle.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.02,1:48:50.65,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors ils grouillent tout autour.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.32,1:48:55.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Les journalistes, les rédacteurs,\Nles critiques,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.49,1:48:57.99,FR,,0,0,0,,des bonnes femmes en permanence.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.66,1:49:01.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Tout le monde réclame :\N"Allez, allez !"
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.00,1:49:07.50,FR,,0,0,0,,Quel foutu écrivain suis-je,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.50,1:49:10.84,FR,,0,0,0,,si je hais l'écriture ?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.71,1:49:14.21,FR,,0,0,0,,Si écrire est un supplice,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.43,1:49:16.77,FR,,0,0,0,,une activité douloureuse\Net humiliante,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.01,1:49:19.56,FR,,0,0,0,,comme de pincer des hémorroïdes ?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.68,1:49:26.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Je pensais que mes livres\Nrendraient les gens meilleurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.81,1:49:29.10,FR,,0,0,0,,Or, personne n'a besoin de moi.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.32,1:49:30.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Et si je crève,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.65,1:49:34.65,FR,,0,0,0,,deux jours après, je serai oublié\Net remplacé par quelqu'un d'autre.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.57,1:49:41.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Je pensais les changer,\Nmais c'est moi qu'ils ont changé
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.99,1:49:44.91,FR,,0,0,0,,et fait à leur image,\Nselon leur ressemblance.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.54,1:49:54.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Autrefois, l'avenir était\Nle prolongement du présent.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.38,1:49:58.18,FR,,0,0,0,,Les changements se profilaient loin,\Nderrière l'horizon.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.14,1:50:02.31,FR,,0,0,0,,À présent, l'avenir se confond\Navec le présent.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.69,1:50:11.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Sont-ils prêts à cela ?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:12.82,1:50:17.33,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils ne veulent rien savoir,\Nils ne font que s'empiffrer.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:31.63,1:50:33.47,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous en avez de la chance.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.38,1:50:36.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Mon Dieu, à présent,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:36.97,1:50:39.27,FR,,0,0,0,,vous allez vivre cent ans.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.40,1:50:57.53,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi pas éternellement ?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.36,1:51:02.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Comme le Juif qui erre,\Néternellement ?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.91,1:51:45.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous êtes sûrement\Nun homme merveilleux.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.08,1:51:48.25,FR,,0,0,0,,Je n'en ai jamais douté.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.25,1:51:53.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous avez supporté\Nun tel martyre !
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.38,1:51:58.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce tunnel est un endroit terrible,\Nle plus terrible de la Zone.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.25,1:52:01.30,FR,,0,0,0,,On l'appelle le hachoir,\Nmais il est pire que ça.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.51,1:52:03.26,FR,,0,0,0,,Combien ont péri ici !
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.47,1:52:11.93,FR,,0,0,0,,Porc-épic y a sacrifié son frère.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.11,1:52:17.36,FR,,0,0,0,,Un garçon si fin, si doué.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.03,1:52:21.53,FR,,0,0,0,,Écoutez plutôt.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.49,1:52:27.70,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Voilà l'été passé\NComme s'il n'avait jamais existé{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.66,1:52:32.96,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}La chaleur subsiste\NMais cela ne suffit pas{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.75,1:52:38.80,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tout ce qui pouvait arriver\NM'est tombé dans les mains{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.59,1:52:44.18,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Telle une feuille à cinq doigts\NMais cela ne suffit pas{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.18,1:52:49.73,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ni le mal ni le bien\NN'ont existé en vain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:50.52,1:52:54.98,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ils ont brûlé d'un feu clair\NMais cela ne suffit pas{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.85,1:53:00.65,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}La vie m'a pris sous son aile\NM'a protégé et sauvé{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.28,1:53:05.62,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}J'ai eu de la chance, c'est vrai\NMais cela ne suffit pas{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.62,1:53:11.54,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Les feuilles n'ont pas brûlé\NLes branches n'ont pas cassé{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.12,1:53:17.25,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Le jour est clair comme du verre\NMais cela ne suffit pas{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.30,1:53:22.01,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est beau, non ? C'est de lui.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.21,1:53:24.80,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est quoi ces simagrées ?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.01,1:53:26.22,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est beau...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.43,1:53:28.43,FR,,0,0,0,,- Je voulais...\N- C'est écœurant.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.64,1:53:31.14,FR,,0,0,0,,Si vous saviez comme je suis heureux.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.35,1:53:35.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Il est rare que tout le monde\Narrive à destination.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.98,1:53:39.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous êtes bons et honnêtes,\Nje suis fier d'avoir vu juste.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.73,1:53:43.48,FR,,0,0,0,,Le voilà fou de joie\Nque tout se soit bien passé.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.65,1:53:47.65,FR,,0,0,0,,Le Destin, la Zone,\Nje suis un homme admirable...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.20,1:53:51.04,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu crois que je n'ai pas vu\Ntes allumettes ?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.24,1:53:53.74,FR,,0,0,0,,- Vous ne comprenez pas...\N- C'est ça, oui.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.91,1:53:56.16,FR,,0,0,0,,Professeur,\Nje ne veux pas vous heurter,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.37,1:53:58.83,FR,,0,0,0,,mais ce vaurien a fait de vous\Nson chouchou,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.04,1:54:00.42,FR,,0,0,0,,pour une raison inconnue.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:00.63,1:54:02.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi dites-vous ça ?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.46,1:54:06.46,FR,,0,0,0,,Et moi, individu inférieur,\Nje suis bon pour le tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.63,1:54:08.92,FR,,0,0,0,,Le hachoir, quel mot !
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.14,1:54:14.98,FR,,0,0,0,,De quel droit choisis-tu qui survit\Net qui passe par le hachoir ?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.31,1:54:17.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi je ne choisis rien, c'est vous.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.56,1:54:21.77,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi ? J'ai choisi\Nentre deux allumettes longues.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.32,1:54:24.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Les allumettes, ce n'est rien.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.49,1:54:28.41,FR,,0,0,0,,Déjà avec l'écrou j'ai vu\Nque la Zone vous laissait passer,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.61,1:54:31.57,FR,,0,0,0,,et que vous pourriez franchir\Nle hachoir,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:32.03,1:54:33.16,FR,,0,0,0,,et nous après vous.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.33,1:54:34.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça alors !
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.58,1:54:40.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne choisis jamais moi-même.\NC'est terrifiant de se tromper.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.50,1:54:43.63,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais il faut bien un premier.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.05,1:54:45.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Oui ?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.34,1:54:47.80,FR,,0,0,0,,Non, ce n'est pas une clinique !
Dialogue: 0,1:54:49.26,1:54:52.76,FR,,0,0,0,,Quelqu'un doit passer en premier.\NVoyez-vous ça !
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.98,1:55:01.32,FR,,0,0,0,,N'y touchez pas !
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.04,1:55:25.58,FR,,0,0,0,,Laboratoire n° 9, je vous prie.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.59,1:55:27.97,FR,,0,0,0,,Une minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.51,1:55:35.51,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Allô j'écoute.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.72,1:55:37.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne te dérange pas ?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.68,1:55:39.14,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Que veux-tu ?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.48,1:55:44.82,FR,,0,0,0,,En deux mots.\NVous l'avez cachée, je l'ai trouvée.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.02,1:55:47.73,FR,,0,0,0,,Dans l'ancien bâtiment,\Nquatrième bunker.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.45,1:55:50.62,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu m'entends ?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:50.82,1:55:53.82,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}J'avise immédiatement\Nle service de sécurité.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.03,1:55:55.11,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu peux.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.53,1:55:58.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Avise qui tu veux,\Nécris tes lettres de dénonciation,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:59.12,1:56:03.38,FR,,0,0,0,,monte mes collaborateurs contre moi,\Nc'est trop tard.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:03.54,1:56:06.46,FR,,0,0,0,,Je suis à deux pas\Nde l'endroit en question.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.96,1:56:09.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu m'entends ?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:09.80,1:56:12.43,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ce sera la fin de ta carrière\Nde chercheur.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.63,1:56:13.63,FR,,0,0,0,,Réjouis-t'en.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.80,1:56:17.18,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tu sais ce qui va arriver,\Nsi tu oses ?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:19.48,1:56:21.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu veux encore me faire peur.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.10,1:56:26.73,FR,,0,0,0,,Toute ma vie,\Nj'ai eu peur de quelque chose.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.19,1:56:28.98,FR,,0,0,0,,J'ai même eu peur de toi.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:29.36,1:56:32.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais à présent,\Nplus rien ne m'effraie.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.95,1:56:36.20,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tu n'es même pas un Érostrate.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.41,1:56:39.50,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tu as toujours essayé\Nde me faire des crasses,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:39.70,1:56:43.16,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}parce qu'il y a 20 ans\Nj'ai couché avec ta femme.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:43.37,1:56:47.42,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Alors tu es ravi de pouvoir\Nme régler mon compte.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:47.88,1:56:52.18,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Vas-y, fais-la, ta saloperie.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.17,1:56:55.21,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Je te défends de raccrocher.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:56.68,1:57:00.02,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}La prison n'est pas le pire\Nde ce qui t'attend.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.22,1:57:03.22,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Car tu ne te le pardonneras jamais.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.39,1:57:04.72,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Je t'y vois déjà,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:04.94,1:57:08.19,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}pendu à tes bretelles\Nau-dessus des latrines.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.98,1:57:14.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Que manigancez-vous, Professeur ?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:15.86,1:57:20.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Qu'arrivera-t-il quand tout le monde\Ncroira en cette Chambre
Dialogue: 0,1:57:22.12,1:57:25.29,FR,,0,0,0,,et que tout le monde se ruera ici ?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:26.17,1:57:30.09,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce n'est qu'une question de temps.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:30.25,1:57:33.55,FR,,0,0,0,,Demain ils accourront par milliers.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.76,1:57:35.85,FR,,0,0,0,,Tous ces empereurs avortés,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.01,1:57:39.01,FR,,0,0,0,,ces grands inquisiteurs\Net autres führers.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:39.22,1:57:43.18,FR,,0,0,0,,Tous ces bienfaiteurs du genre humain\Nqui viendront
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.35,1:57:47.98,FR,,0,0,0,,non par appât du gain,\Nmais pour changer le monde.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:48.19,1:57:50.03,FR,,0,0,0,,Non, je ne prends pas ceux-là.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:50.23,1:57:53.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment le savez-vous ?\NVous êtes drôle, vous.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:53.94,1:57:56.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous n'êtes pas l'unique Stalker\Nau monde.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.78,1:57:59.87,FR,,0,0,0,,Et aucun Stalker ne sait\Nce qu'apportent
Dialogue: 0,1:58:00.08,1:58:03.12,FR,,0,0,0,,ou emportent d'ici\Nceux qu'il y amène.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.33,1:58:06.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Le nombre de crimes\Nsans mobile augmente.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.50,1:58:08.13,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous n'y êtes pour rien ?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.29,1:58:10.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Et les coups d'État militaires ?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.46,1:58:15.55,FR,,0,0,0,,Les mafieux dans les gouvernements\Nne sont pas vos clients ?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:15.76,1:58:17.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Et les lasers,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:17.59,1:58:19.93,FR,,0,0,0,,les super-bactéries,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:20.14,1:58:24.48,FR,,0,0,0,,ces horreurs infectes encore cachées\Ndans les coffres-forts ?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:24.68,1:58:27.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Arrêtez cette diarrhée sociologique.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.81,1:58:29.94,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous croyez à toutes ces légendes ?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.15,1:58:31.86,FR,,0,0,0,,Aux légendes effrayantes, oui.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:32.07,1:58:34.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Aux belles légendes, certainement pas.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:34.90,1:58:36.44,FR,,0,0,0,,Arrêtez ça.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:37.03,1:58:43.00,FR,,0,0,0,,Un seul être ne peut pas éprouver\Nune haine ou un amour tels
Dialogue: 0,1:58:43.16,1:58:46.08,FR,,0,0,0,,qu'ils s'étendent\Nà l'humanité entière.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:47.04,1:58:50.79,FR,,0,0,0,,Désirer de l'argent, une femme,\Nune vengeance,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:50.96,1:58:54.92,FR,,0,0,0,,ou que son chef se fasse écraser,\Npasse encore.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:55.13,1:58:56.84,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais diriger le monde,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:57.01,1:59:00.64,FR,,0,0,0,,une société juste,\Nle règne de Dieu sur la Terre,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.80,1:59:04.55,FR,,0,0,0,,ce ne sont pas des souhaits\Nmais des idéologies, des actions,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:04.77,1:59:05.94,FR,,0,0,0,,des conceptions.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:07.18,1:59:11.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Une compassion inconsciente\Nne peut encore se matérialiser,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:12.48,1:59:15.53,FR,,0,0,0,,comme un désir instinctif ordinaire.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:15.94,1:59:20.19,FR,,0,0,0,,Peut-on construire son bonheur\Nsur le malheur d'autrui ?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:21.07,1:59:25.07,FR,,0,0,0,,Je vois bien que\Nvous souhaitez écraser l'humanité
Dialogue: 0,1:59:25.29,1:59:28.50,FR,,0,0,0,,sous le poids\Nd'une bonne action fabuleuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:29.33,1:59:31.21,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais je suis tranquille,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:31.92,1:59:33.76,FR,,0,0,0,,et pour vous et pour moi,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:33.92,1:59:36.17,FR,,0,0,0,,et encore plus pour l'humanité.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.46,1:59:39.84,FR,,0,0,0,,Car vous n'arriverez à rien.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.97,1:59:44.68,FR,,0,0,0,,Au mieux,\Nvous recevrez votre prix Nobel.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:46.31,1:59:51.48,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais a priori il vous arrivera\Nquelque chose de très incongru
Dialogue: 0,1:59:51.69,1:59:55.53,FR,,0,0,0,,qui ne vous serait jamais\Nvenu à l'esprit.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:57.73,2:00:02.28,FR,,0,0,0,,On rêve d'une chose\Net il en arrive une autre.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:04.12,2:00:05.75,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi faites-vous ça ?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:20.13,2:00:21.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Le téléphone.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:22.18,2:00:23.81,FR,,0,0,0,,L'électricité...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:27.72,2:00:30.89,FR,,0,0,0,,Regardez,\Nc'est un excellent somnifère.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:31.23,2:00:35.23,FR,,0,0,0,,On ne le trouve plus nulle part\Net ici, il y en a plein.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:39.32,2:00:41.15,FR,,0,0,0,,On y va ?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:42.40,2:00:43.94,FR,,0,0,0,,La nuit va bientôt tomber.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:45.03,2:00:46.95,FR,,0,0,0,,Il fera nuit pour le retour.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:53.92,2:00:57.67,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi, j'ai très bien compris
Dialogue: 0,2:00:57.88,2:01:01.38,FR,,0,0,0,,que le fait de réciter des poèmes\Net de tourner en rond
Dialogue: 0,2:01:01.55,2:01:05.01,FR,,0,0,0,,n'est qu'une façon originale\Nde présenter des excuses.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:05.22,2:01:06.72,FR,,0,0,0,,Je vous comprends.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:08.93,2:01:11.68,FR,,0,0,0,,Une enfance difficile,\Nle contexte social...
Dialogue: 0,2:01:12.60,2:01:15.02,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne vous faites pas d'illusions.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:17.48,2:01:19.52,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne vous pardonnerai pas.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:20.03,2:01:22.49,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne faites pas ça, je vous en prie.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:14.79,2:02:17.96,FR,,0,0,0,,Professeur, revenez vers nous.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:51.70,2:02:53.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Attendez.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:53.70,2:02:55.16,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne vous pressez pas.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:55.37,2:02:57.54,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne me presse pas du tout.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:48.47,2:03:50.81,FR,,0,0,0,,Je sais que ça va vous contrarier
Dialogue: 0,2:03:53.64,2:03:56.10,FR,,0,0,0,,mais je dois quand même\Nvous le dire.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:02.81,2:04:04.52,FR,,0,0,0,,Nous nous trouvons là
Dialogue: 0,2:04:06.28,2:04:07.95,FR,,0,0,0,,au seuil.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:15.33,2:04:17.62,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est le moment le plus important
Dialogue: 0,2:04:19.16,2:04:20.58,FR,,0,0,0,,de votre vie.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:23.58,2:04:25.16,FR,,0,0,0,,Sachez qu'ici
Dialogue: 0,2:04:27.05,2:04:32.01,FR,,0,0,0,,votre souhait le plus cher\Nsera exaucé.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:33.89,2:04:36.10,FR,,0,0,0,,Votre souhait le plus sincère.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:37.89,2:04:39.77,FR,,0,0,0,,Le plus douloureux.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:09.00,2:05:10.96,FR,,0,0,0,,Il n'y a pas besoin de parler.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:14.30,2:05:15.76,FR,,0,0,0,,Il faut juste
Dialogue: 0,2:05:18.10,2:05:19.64,FR,,0,0,0,,se concentrer
Dialogue: 0,2:05:20.27,2:05:23.52,FR,,0,0,0,,et essayer de se rappeler\Ntoute sa vie.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:26.40,2:05:31.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Quand l'homme pense à son passé,\Nil devient meilleur.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:32.82,2:05:34.57,FR,,0,0,0,,Le principal...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:08.15,2:06:09.44,FR,,0,0,0,,Le principal,
Dialogue: 0,2:06:14.53,2:06:15.91,FR,,0,0,0,,c'est de croire.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:25.33,2:06:27.04,FR,,0,0,0,,Maintenant, allez-y.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:32.92,2:06:34.59,FR,,0,0,0,,Qui passe le premier ?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:39.85,2:06:41.14,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous, peut-être ?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:43.06,2:06:46.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi ? Non, je ne veux pas.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:47.19,2:06:49.19,FR,,0,0,0,,Je sais, ce n'est pas facile.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:49.36,2:06:51.82,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne craignez rien, ça passera.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:53.61,2:06:58.11,FR,,0,0,0,,Cela m'étonnerait que ça passe.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:00.12,2:07:03.83,FR,,0,0,0,,D'abord,\Nje doute que le souvenir de mon passé
Dialogue: 0,2:07:05.37,2:07:06.95,FR,,0,0,0,,me rende meilleur.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:09.04,2:07:13.92,FR,,0,0,0,,Et puis, ne sens-tu pas\Nà quel point c'est bas ?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:31.73,2:07:33.11,FR,,0,0,0,,S'abaisser,
Dialogue: 0,2:07:34.61,2:07:36.90,FR,,0,0,0,,pleurnicher, prier ?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:38.03,2:07:40.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Qu'y a-t-il de mal dans la prière ?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:42.28,2:07:44.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous dites ça par orgueil.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:46.12,2:07:49.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Calmez-vous,\Nvous n'êtes pas encore prêt.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:49.29,2:07:51.21,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça arrive assez souvent.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:54.00,2:07:55.96,FR,,0,0,0,,Voulez-vous passer le premier ?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:04.05,2:08:05.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi ?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:16.11,2:08:18.20,FR,,0,0,0,,Voilà, sous vos yeux,
Dialogue: 0,2:08:18.40,2:08:21.74,FR,,0,0,0,,la nouvelle invention\Ndu "professeur Professeur".
Dialogue: 0,2:08:22.24,2:08:26.41,FR,,0,0,0,,Un appareil pour étudier l'âme,\Nun âmomètre.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:26.91,2:08:28.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce n'est qu'une bombe.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:29.62,2:08:30.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment ?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:33.00,2:08:34.46,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est une blague.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:34.79,2:08:35.87,FR,,0,0,0,,Non.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:37.88,2:08:40.17,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est juste une bombe.\NVingt kilotonnes.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:41.59,2:08:42.84,FR,,0,0,0,,Pour quoi faire ?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:53.52,2:08:57.48,FR,,0,0,0,,Je l'avais fabriquée\Navec des amis.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:59.53,2:09:03.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Avec mes anciens collègues.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:07.37,2:09:11.37,FR,,0,0,0,,Cet endroit n'apportera de bonheur\Nà personne.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:15.50,2:09:20.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Et s'il tombe\Nentre de mauvaises mains...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:22.55,2:09:24.97,FR,,0,0,0,,Enfin, je ne sais même plus à présent.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:26.76,2:09:28.80,FR,,0,0,0,,On avait pensé à l'époque,
Dialogue: 0,2:09:31.10,2:09:33.90,FR,,0,0,0,,qu'il ne fallait pas détruire la Zone.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:35.48,2:09:41.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Car même si c'est un miracle,\Nc'est une partie de la nature.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:41.90,2:09:44.61,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est donc l'espoir,\Nen un certain sens.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:46.62,2:09:48.87,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils ont donc caché la bombe
Dialogue: 0,2:09:49.87,2:09:51.33,FR,,0,0,0,,et je l'ai retrouvée.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:51.50,2:09:53.96,FR,,0,0,0,,Ancien bâtiment, quatrième bunker.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:59.50,2:10:02.55,FR,,0,0,0,,Il existe certainement un principe :
Dialogue: 0,2:10:04.30,2:10:07.14,FR,,0,0,0,,ne jamais commettre\Nd'actions irréversibles.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:07.34,2:10:09.84,FR,,0,0,0,,Je le comprends, je ne suis pas fou.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:14.06,2:10:16.77,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais tant que cet ulcère\Nsera accessible ici
Dialogue: 0,2:10:17.77,2:10:19.94,FR,,0,0,0,,à n'importe quel salaud,
Dialogue: 0,2:10:22.23,2:10:24.44,FR,,0,0,0,,je n'aurai ni sommeil, ni repos.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:31.91,2:10:35.04,FR,,0,0,0,,À moins que mon for intérieur\Nne me l'interdise ?
Dialogue: 0,2:10:41.25,2:10:44.25,FR,,0,0,0,,Le pauvre,\Nil s'est posé une belle colle.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:07.99,2:11:09.07,FR,,0,0,0,,Donnez-moi ça.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:24.09,2:11:25.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Donnez-moi ça !
Dialogue: 0,2:11:30.68,2:11:32.89,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais où sont passées vos manières ?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:40.23,2:11:41.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi faites-vous cela ?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:42.19,2:11:44.23,FR,,0,0,0,,Espèce d'ordure hypocrite.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:45.65,2:11:49.82,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi me traitez-vous ainsi ?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:50.82,2:11:52.61,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est lui qui veut tout détruire.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:52.82,2:11:55.45,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est votre espoir\Nqu'il veut détruire !
Dialogue: 0,2:12:18.18,2:12:21.85,FR,,0,0,0,,Il n'est plus rien resté\Naux hommes sur Terre.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:22.85,2:12:27.31,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est l'unique endroit\Noù l'on peut venir
Dialogue: 0,2:12:27.90,2:12:30.07,FR,,0,0,0,,lorsqu'il n'y a plus aucun espoir.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:32.49,2:12:34.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous êtes bien venus, vous !
Dialogue: 0,2:12:34.99,2:12:37.95,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi détruisez-vous la foi ?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:38.16,2:12:40.20,FR,,0,0,0,,Vas-tu te taire ?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:42.83,2:12:45.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Je vois clair en toi.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:46.30,2:12:48.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu t'en fous, des gens.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:49.59,2:12:52.05,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu gagnes de l'argent
Dialogue: 0,2:12:54.18,2:12:55.43,FR,,0,0,0,,sur notre tourment.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:55.64,2:12:58.64,FR,,0,0,0,,Et même sans argent,\Ntu prends du plaisir ici,
Dialogue: 0,2:12:58.85,2:13:02.19,FR,,0,0,0,,car tu y es tout-puissant,\Nordure hypocrite.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:02.39,2:13:05.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu décides de notre vie\Nou de notre mort.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:05.27,2:13:07.61,FR,,0,0,0,,Dire que c'est lui qui choisit !
Dialogue: 0,2:13:09.11,2:13:13.45,FR,,0,0,0,,Voilà pourquoi les Stalkers\Nn'entrent jamais dans la Chambre.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:13.61,2:13:14.94,FR,,0,0,0,,Pour quoi faire,
Dialogue: 0,2:13:15.28,2:13:19.08,FR,,0,0,0,,si ici vous pouvez savourer\Nle pouvoir et l'autorité ?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:19.29,2:13:20.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Que désirer de plus ?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:21.33,2:13:24.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce n'est pas vrai, vous vous trompez.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:29.96,2:13:33.46,FR,,0,0,0,,Un Stalker n'a pas le droit d'entrer\Ndans la Chambre
Dialogue: 0,2:13:34.05,2:13:36.97,FR,,0,0,0,,ni d'aller dans la Zone\Ndans un but intéressé.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:37.35,2:13:39.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Souvenez-vous de Porc-épic.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:41.89,2:13:44.23,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est vrai,\Nje ne suis qu'une ordure.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:44.40,2:13:47.94,FR,,0,0,0,,Je n'ai rien fait dans ce monde\Net ne puis rien faire.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:49.94,2:13:52.49,FR,,0,0,0,,Je n'ai rien pu donner à ma femme.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:53.40,2:13:55.86,FR,,0,0,0,,Je n'ai pas d'amis\Net je ne puis en avoir.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:56.41,2:13:58.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais ne m'enlevez pas\Nce qui est à moi.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:58.87,2:14:02.25,FR,,0,0,0,,On m'a déjà tout pris là-bas,\Nderrière les barbelés.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:06.08,2:14:09.54,FR,,0,0,0,,Ce qui m'appartient est ici même,
Dialogue: 0,2:14:10.25,2:14:11.50,FR,,0,0,0,,dans la Zone.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:13.05,2:14:17.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Mon bonheur, ma liberté,\Nma dignité, tout est là.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:19.85,2:14:23.23,FR,,0,0,0,,Je conduis ici des gens comme moi,\Ndes malheureux.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:23.56,2:14:27.40,FR,,0,0,0,,Il ne leur reste plus aucun espoir.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:28.81,2:14:33.02,FR,,0,0,0,,Et personne d'autre que moi\Nne peut les aider.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:33.36,2:14:35.11,FR,,0,0,0,,Je peux, moi, l'ordure !
Dialogue: 0,2:14:37.45,2:14:40.20,FR,,0,0,0,,J'en pleure de bonheur de les aider.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:41.45,2:14:43.74,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est tout, je ne veux rien de plus.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:06.35,2:15:08.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Peut-être bien.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:09.10,2:15:11.31,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors, excuse-moi,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:12.90,2:15:15.07,FR,,0,0,0,,mais tu n'es qu'un simple d'esprit.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:17.11,2:15:20.24,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu n'as aucune idée\Nde ce qui se passe ici.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:24.08,2:15:27.21,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi Porc-épic\Ns'est-il pendu, selon toi ?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:27.41,2:15:31.08,FR,,0,0,0,,Il est venu dans un but intéressé\Net à cause de l'argent,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:31.29,2:15:34.04,FR,,0,0,0,,il a fait périr son frère\Ndans le hachoir.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:34.25,2:15:37.67,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais pourquoi s'est-il pendu\Nmalgré tout ?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:38.30,2:15:39.89,FR,,0,0,0,,Pourquoi n'est-il pas revenu,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:40.09,2:15:42.64,FR,,0,0,0,,non pour l'argent,\Nmais pour son frère ?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:43.68,2:15:45.27,FR,,0,0,0,,Puisqu'il s'était repenti ?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:45.56,2:15:49.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Il le voulait mais peu après,\Nil s'est pendu.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:50.10,2:15:52.81,FR,,0,0,0,,Il a compris que dans la Chambre,
Dialogue: 0,2:15:53.57,2:15:56.87,FR,,0,0,0,,seuls les vœux les plus secrets\Nétaient exaucés.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:04.49,2:16:07.16,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu peux crier autant que tu veux.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:15.38,2:16:19.51,FR,,0,0,0,,Ici se réalise ce qui correspond\Nà ta nature profonde
Dialogue: 0,2:16:19.93,2:16:22.85,FR,,0,0,0,,que tu ne soupçonnes même pas
Dialogue: 0,2:16:23.05,2:16:25.30,FR,,0,0,0,,et qui dirige toute ta vie.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:26.60,2:16:29.02,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu n'as rien compris.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:29.18,2:16:31.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Porc-épic n'a pas cédé à la cupidité.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:31.60,2:16:34.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Il a supplié son frère à genoux\Ndans cette même mare.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:35.19,2:16:40.03,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais n'a reçu que des masses d'argent\Net rien d'autre.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:41.20,2:16:44.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Car Porc-épic, c'est Porc-épic\Net rien d'autre.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:44.78,2:16:49.12,FR,,0,0,0,,La conscience et les états d'âme,\Nc'est imaginaire.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:49.83,2:16:52.00,FR,,0,0,0,,Il l'a compris et s'est pendu.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:56.92,2:16:58.88,FR,,0,0,0,,Je n'irai pas dans ta Chambre.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:00.72,2:17:03.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne veux pas déverser\Ntoutes mes saletés
Dialogue: 0,2:17:03.68,2:17:05.56,FR,,0,0,0,,sur la tête d'autrui,
Dialogue: 0,2:17:06.10,2:17:07.44,FR,,0,0,0,,même la tienne,
Dialogue: 0,2:17:08.43,2:17:11.06,FR,,0,0,0,,pour me pendre ensuite,\Ncomme Porc-épic.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:12.06,2:17:17.02,FR,,0,0,0,,Je préfère me noyer dans l'alcool\Nà notre Club des Écrivains.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:19.57,2:17:24.58,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu ne connais rien aux gens,\NGrand-Serpent,
Dialogue: 0,2:17:25.37,2:17:28.46,FR,,0,0,0,,si tu conduis dans la Zone\Ndes types comme moi.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:35.92,2:17:37.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Et après tout,
Dialogue: 0,2:17:39.25,2:17:43.30,FR,,0,0,0,,qui t'a fait croire\Nque ce miracle peut avoir lieu ?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:44.76,2:17:49.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Qui vous a dit que les vœux\Nétaient exaucés ici ?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:51.85,2:17:55.90,FR,,0,0,0,,Avez-vous vu un seul homme\Nsortant d'ici comblé ?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:57.73,2:17:59.48,FR,,0,0,0,,Porc-épic peut-être ?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:04.49,2:18:07.29,FR,,0,0,0,,Au fait, qui vous a parlé
Dialogue: 0,2:18:07.49,2:18:12.24,FR,,0,0,0,,de la Zone, de Porc-épic,\Nde la Chambre ?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:14.37,2:18:15.62,FR,,0,0,0,,Lui.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:20.56,2:19:22.94,FR,,0,0,0,,Alors, je n'y comprends rien.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:24.57,2:19:27.16,FR,,0,0,0,,Quel sens y a-t-il de venir ici ?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:50.53,2:20:51.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Quel silence.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:53.70,2:20:54.91,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous entendez ?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:00.46,2:21:03.88,FR,,0,0,0,,Et si je laissais tout tomber ?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:05.46,2:21:10.01,FR,,0,0,0,,Si je prenais ma femme et Ouistiti\Npour venir vivre ici.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:13.59,2:21:14.88,FR,,0,0,0,,Pour toujours.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:17.47,2:21:19.22,FR,,0,0,0,,Il n'y a personne ici.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:20.35,2:21:22.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Personne ne leur ferait de mal.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:37.15,2:25:38.69,FR,,0,0,0,,Te voilà revenu.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:45.03,2:25:46.78,FR,,0,0,0,,Ça vient d'où, ça ?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:48.24,2:25:49.53,FR,,0,0,0,,Il nous a suivis.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:50.75,2:25:52.67,FR,,0,0,0,,On n'allait pas le laisser.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:10.02,2:26:12.48,FR,,0,0,0,,Bon... On y va ?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:13.60,2:26:15.10,FR,,0,0,0,,Ouistiti attend.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:19.23,2:26:20.65,FR,,0,0,0,,On y va ?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:35.12,2:26:37.58,FR,,0,0,0,,Personne n'a besoin d'un chien ?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:40.67,2:26:42.80,FR,,0,0,0,,J'en ai cinq comme ça chez moi.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:52.93,2:26:55.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous aimez les chiens alors ?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:56.23,2:26:57.32,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment ?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:57.60,2:26:59.02,FR,,0,0,0,,C'est très bien.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:04.82,2:27:07.03,FR,,0,0,0,,Allez, en route.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:10.09,2:30:12.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Si vous saviez comme je suis fatigué.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:14.26,2:30:15.76,FR,,0,0,0,,Dieu seul le sait.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:17.97,2:30:22.43,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils se prétendent intellectuels,\Nces écrivains, ces chercheurs !
Dialogue: 0,2:30:22.64,2:30:23.89,FR,,0,0,0,,Calme-toi.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:24.81,2:30:26.81,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils ne croient en rien.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:27.52,2:30:28.56,FR,,0,0,0,,Chez eux,
Dialogue: 0,2:30:29.86,2:30:32.24,FR,,0,0,0,,l'organe de la foi est atrophié.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:32.49,2:30:35.24,FR,,0,0,0,,- Calme-toi.\N- Car il ne leur sert jamais.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:36.28,2:30:39.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Calme-toi, viens te coucher.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:40.37,2:30:41.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Viens.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:42.83,2:30:45.38,FR,,0,0,0,,Il fait humide,\Nc'est mauvais pour toi.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:48.54,2:30:49.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Enlève ça.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:01.45,2:32:03.24,FR,,0,0,0,,Seigneur, que sont ces gens.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:03.45,2:32:04.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Calme-toi.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:05.04,2:32:07.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Calme-toi, ce n'est pas leur faute.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:07.83,2:32:10.46,FR,,0,0,0,,Il faut les plaindre\Net toi tu te fâches.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:10.67,2:32:13.34,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu as vu leurs yeux,\Nils sont vides.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:25.85,2:32:28.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils ne pensent qu'à se faire valoir,
Dialogue: 0,2:32:29.31,2:32:32.06,FR,,0,0,0,,à se vendre au meilleur prix.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:32.27,2:32:34.98,FR,,0,0,0,,À se faire payer chaque élan de l'âme.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:38.19,2:32:41.07,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils considèrent ne pas être nés\Npour rien,
Dialogue: 0,2:32:41.28,2:32:42.66,FR,,0,0,0,,être choisis.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:45.58,2:32:47.58,FR,,0,0,0,,Ils ne vivent qu'une fois.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:49.58,2:32:52.67,FR,,0,0,0,,Comment peuvent-ils croire\Nen quelque chose ?
Dialogue: 0,2:32:53.84,2:32:56.30,FR,,0,0,0,,Calme-toi, ne parle plus.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:57.76,2:32:59.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Essaie de dormir.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:05.68,2:33:09.31,FR,,0,0,0,,Personne ne croit,\Npas seulement ces deux-là.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:10.56,2:33:11.69,FR,,0,0,0,,Personne.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:12.40,2:33:14.49,FR,,0,0,0,,Qui vais-je emmener là-bas ?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:18.53,2:33:19.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Seigneur.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:20.78,2:33:22.28,FR,,0,0,0,,Le plus terrible,
Dialogue: 0,2:33:24.95,2:33:29.08,FR,,0,0,0,,c'est que personne n'en a besoin,\Nde cette Chambre.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:29.29,2:33:31.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Tous mes efforts ne servent à rien.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:32.04,2:33:34.00,FR,,0,0,0,,Ne dis pas ça.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:34.59,2:33:35.80,FR,,0,0,0,,Arrête.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:41.93,2:33:44.35,FR,,0,0,0,,Je n'y emmènerai plus jamais personne.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:47.26,2:33:51.60,FR,,0,0,0,,Veux-tu que moi, j'y aille avec toi ?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:52.48,2:33:53.73,FR,,0,0,0,,Où ça ?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:54.10,2:33:57.14,FR,,0,0,0,,Tu crois que je n'aurais rien\Nà demander ?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:01.53,2:34:02.74,FR,,0,0,0,,Non.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:06.78,2:34:09.33,FR,,0,0,0,,- Ce n'est pas possible.\N- Pourquoi ?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:12.37,2:34:13.66,FR,,0,0,0,,Non, non.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:18.80,2:34:22.47,FR,,0,0,0,,Et si toi aussi tu échouais ?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:58.67,2:35:01.88,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous savez,\Nma mère était tout à fait contre.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:04.01,2:35:08.39,FR,,0,0,0,,Vous avez bien compris\Nque c'était un bienheureux.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:11.56,2:35:13.73,FR,,0,0,0,,Tout le monde se moquait de lui.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:13.93,2:35:16.72,FR,,0,0,0,,Il avait l'air bête.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:19.32,2:35:20.49,FR,,0,0,0,,Maman disait :
Dialogue: 0,2:35:21.65,2:35:23.03,FR,,0,0,0,,"C'est un Stalker.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:23.23,2:35:26.48,FR,,0,0,0,,"Un condamné à mort,\Nun forçat à perpétuité.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:26.66,2:35:29.00,FR,,0,0,0,,Sais-tu quels enfants\Nont les Stalkers ?"
Dialogue: 0,2:35:29.20,2:35:32.20,FR,,0,0,0,,Moi, je ne le contestais même pas.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:34.96,2:35:37.88,FR,,0,0,0,,Je savais\Nque c'était un condamné à mort.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:38.17,2:35:39.71,FR,,0,0,0,,Prisonnier à vie.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:40.71,2:35:43.17,FR,,0,0,0,,Je savais pour les enfants aussi.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:47.13,2:35:48.72,FR,,0,0,0,,Que pouvais-je faire ?
Dialogue: 0,2:35:48.93,2:35:52.14,FR,,0,0,0,,J'étais sûre\Nqu'avec lui je serais bien.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:54.48,2:35:57.36,FR,,0,0,0,,Je savais\Nqu'il y aurait bien des malheurs
Dialogue: 0,2:35:58.14,2:36:02.73,FR,,0,0,0,,mais un bonheur amer vaut mieux
Dialogue: 0,2:36:04.82,2:36:07.03,FR,,0,0,0,,qu'une vie grise et maussade.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:12.49,2:36:15.41,FR,,0,0,0,,Peut-être ai-je inventé tout cela\Naprès coup.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:24.76,2:36:27.80,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais quand il m'a dit\Ntout simplement :
Dialogue: 0,2:36:27.97,2:36:30.31,FR,,0,0,0,,"Viens avec moi", je l'ai suivi.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:31.35,2:36:33.98,FR,,0,0,0,,Je ne l'ai jamais regretté.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:37.89,2:36:39.10,FR,,0,0,0,,Jamais.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:42.06,2:36:44.15,FR,,0,0,0,,J'ai connu le malheur,
Dialogue: 0,2:36:45.07,2:36:47.24,FR,,0,0,0,,la peur et la honte.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:47.53,2:36:51.24,FR,,0,0,0,,Mais je n'ai jamais regretté\Nni envié personne.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:53.49,2:36:55.12,FR,,0,0,0,,Car c'est le destin.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:56.83,2:36:59.42,FR,,0,0,0,,Ainsi va la vie, nous sommes comme ça.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:04.80,2:37:08.55,FR,,0,0,0,,Sans malheur, notre vie\Nn'aurait pas été meilleure.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:10.18,2:37:11.72,FR,,0,0,0,,Elle aurait été pire.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:14.60,2:37:19.19,FR,,0,0,0,,Car alors,\Nil n'y aurait pas eu de bonheur.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:21.85,2:37:24.06,FR,,0,0,0,,Et il n'y aurait pas eu d'espoir.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:27.53,2:37:28.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Voilà.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:15.37,2:38:18.21,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Comme j'aime tes yeux{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:38:19.16,2:38:22.25,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Et leur flamme étincelante{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:38:23.62,2:38:26.62,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Quand tu les lèves soudain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:38:27.50,2:38:30.38,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tel un éclair surgi des cieux{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:38:30.88,2:38:34.22,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Et traces un grand arc en un instant{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:38:35.14,2:38:38.35,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mais il est des délices{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:38:38.85,2:38:41.94,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Encore plus forts : les yeux inclinés{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:38:42.35,2:38:45.56,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Des baisers fous{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:38:45.94,2:38:49.19,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Et à travers les cils abaissés{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:38:50.19,2:38:56.82,FR,,0,0,0,,{\i1}La flamme sombre et trouble du désir{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,2:41:44.91,2:41:46.45,FR,,0,0,0,,FIN
Dialogue: 0,2:41:46.66,2:41:48.70,FR,,0,0,0,,Studios Mosfilm 1979
